@NODE "Mail_0" "060 and Blitz"
From: mike.child@sbu.ac.uk
Date: Mon, 14 Dec 1998 10:22:19 +0000
Subject: 060 and Blitz


Hello there

I seem to remember someone having a problem with Blitz on an 060 a while ago.

Now its me.

Attempting to compile crashes the machine, sometimes with a suspend/reboot
requester, sometimes just a flashing power light and reset.

The crash occurs even with an empty Ted, also with source code of an
executable which itself runs OK, so its the compilation process itself, not
whats being compiled.

I've changed nothing but the accelerator card (Blizzard 030@50 replaced by
Apollo 060@66). Only commodities I run are Noclick, PowerWB, ToolsDaemon and
Clicktofront. Blitz is 2.1 with BSS/RedDebug.

Haven't had a chance to experiment much yet. Turning off everything on the
cpu (no caches, no anything) made no difference. Checked the Blitz disks and
BSS disks for 060-specific files I might need but couldn't find anything.

Wanted to ask before Christmas!

Any other non-blitz related 060 tips are welcome too - bewildering array of
options on an 060 aren't there? (I have oxypatcher but not in my startup yet).

(Any chance of getting Simon the Sorcerer to run? Why don't Apollos have a
keyboard disable like Blizzard? Grr. I was enjoying STS and now I have to
choose between 51Mips and Mr. Barrie...?)

All suggestions welcome...

Thanks
Mike Child



@ENDNODE
