@NODE "Mail_5" "Re: 060 and Blitz"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    16 Dec 98 09:01:23 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Wed, 16 Dec 1998 09:01:18 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: 060 and Blitz

Hello Mikkel

> Erm, forgive me for asking, but should you not put a Permit_ at the end =
in
> any case, since otherwise the computer wouldn't be able to do anything
> after your program quits ? Just a thought...

 Nah, its normal to put a Fordib_ at the end of your program, if you are 
handling the workbench startup message (WBStartup does this automatically)=
. Its 
done right before you close your final lib (exec) and exit, so no-one can 
interfere with your program exit. Once a Forbid_den program exits, the OS =
knows 
to start up the rest of the tasks again.


