> Is there anyone here who wouuld want to develop a 3D engine as a group, as
> opposed to a single person ? IMHO this would be very cool, and is the most
> productive way of doing a 3D routine.

It's probably best to wait for Warp3D and build an engine based
on that. There's no way you're going to support 3D cards with
Blitz alone and 68k is just not good enough for the kind of thing
you'd want to see in a modern 3D engine.

