 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Mon, 7 Dec 1998 01:06:32 +0000
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Mon, 07 Dec 1998 01:02:58 +0000
Subject: Re: 3D Library
Encoding: quoted-printable

Fr=E9d=E9ric Laboureur churned out *this* drivel :

>    Thanks for the information ! I've took the lib and convert the cube
> example in Blitz 2 source code. It was never so easy to do some 3D
> stuffs... Cool hey ?
 =

> PS:  Thanks James, your NewFDConvert works really good ;=B0).

Of course it does ;)

I converted the lib as well, but got a little bit
frightened by the autodocs (especially as they're in
Italian ;) I tried getting babelfish.altavista.com to translate =

them, but it stopped halfway through (what was converted looked
quite readable though)...maybe someone else wants to try (I converted =

the docs to HTML and uploaded them to my own site, then pointed =

babelfish at it!)...

BTW That demo was very smooth here...tiny executable too...looks =

like a great library :)

Pity I don't have a clue when it comes to 3d maths though...

See ya,
-- =

