@NODE "Mail_29" "3D Polygon Demo - COMPETITION"
From: Jamie Bentley <sniper@technet2000.com.au>
Date: Sat, 05 Dec 1998 10:24:27 +0500
Organization: Sniper Productions
Subject: 3D Polygon Demo - COMPETITION
Encoding: quoted-printable

 Hyea all,

 Stephen Fellner suggested a very good idea to me, about having a competi=
tion
to see who can make the  fastest 3D  polygon engine (light sourcing/possi=
ble
tranpsarent polygons and gourad shading are optional).

 At the moment, there isn't much of a prise, but you get your engine used=
 in a
game.. We'll do all the gfx and sound and plot for you, and you'll get 50=
% of
the income.

 Specifications of the Demo:

 1) Must be able to run in UNDER 8 meg.
 2) Sizable screens (320x256 to 128x100 etc)
 3) Must have at least one example of light sourcing.
 4) Must be OS Friendly (AMIGA + N  should bring you back to the workbenc=
h
while demo runs in BG).

 In order not to make the demo too hard.. There can be no sound (a tracke=
r in
the background if you really must).

 I thank for reading this, if you wish to enter Return this email to ME (=
not
the Blitz list) with your Name, email address, Amiga setup and list of 3D=

games you've played (IE: Doom, Quake, Quake 2 etc).

 Also give me an estimate time of when you'll have it finished.

 I'll base the entry time on the average "estimated time to completion",
because I'm no programmer and I don't know how long these things take.

Jamie Bentley - Sniper Productions=A9 1995
