@NODE "Mail_30" "Re: 3D Polygons"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@sdv.fr>
Date: Tue, 01 Dec 1998 18:57:46 +0100
Organization: Fantaisie Software
Subject: Re: 3D Polygons
Encoding: quoted-printable

    Hi All,

> Hi,
> =

>> Me and a select group of people are taking on a project that will invo=
lve
>> a large 3D engine, much like Quake.
>> The reason I'm asking on a BLITZ list is because there will be no real=

>> textures, just polygons. Like most VR games really.
> =

> I thought all modern 3D games used textured polygons or at least
> gouraud shaded ones. Still, it's all perfectly possible to do this in
> Blitz, especially if you're up to speed with Asm.

    You should check the 'Wild' package on the Aminet which seems to brin=
g a
very good 3D api for the Amiga (a bit like direct 3D, on PC). The demos a=
re
amazing, running fast on 1230/50 Amiga (Both, textured, complex scene, wi=
th
kinetic movement). Hey, Paul West, he use an unknow C2P which use the
Blitter but have the buffer in Fast Ram. I've mailed the author, and he s=
ays
it runs at 40 fps on 1230/50 amiga but it has all the CPU FREE for the
rendering, so is proggy can runs really at 40 fps..

        Bye,

                        Fred.

