Frederic,

>     You should check the 'Wild' package on the Aminet which seems to bring a
> very good 3D api for the Amiga (a bit like direct 3D, on PC). The demos are
> amazing, running fast on 1230/50 Amiga (Both, textured, complex scene, with
> kinetic movement). Hey, Paul West, he use an unknow C2P which use the
> Blitter but have the buffer in Fast Ram. I've mailed the author, and he says
> it runs at 40 fps on 1230/50 amiga but it has all the CPU FREE for the
