Sounds nice. Mind you that would probably only apply to lower-end
cpu's. But if you can get any further information/sourcecode about it
then maybe we can have a look at implementing it into Mildred if it
does indeed perform as you say.

I've been thinking of getting one of those ateo pixel64 gfx-cards
myself so that I can get at least double the performance of c2p on
my system. Anyone here got one?

