Surely that depends on the cpu?? 15fps on an 020 is a lot different to 15fps
on an 060.

>This project would require MASSIVE amounts of optimization and would also
>need gourad shading (optional for the player).
>With the possibility of tranpsarent polygons to simulate water and glass
etc.
>It would also need to be able to manipluate certain parts of the level,
like
>blowing out windows..

>
>Includes are level editor, "character bone maker" (easy animation of 3D
>enemies) etc. (Oh, and it would be cool if the level editor was like VR,
you
>can see the level as your making it).


My advice..tweak some already tried and tested code...reinventing the wheel
is pretty useless, unless you have made a faster or better looking wheel
that is. Why not add stuff  to AB3DII engine (that did better than 15fps
didn`t it??), or use something like crystal space (dunno how fast that
is..on the pc it was ok) or even at worse you could try open gl (hmmm..not
sure about that..it`s not amazingly fast on the pc).

Good luck with the project,

Dave

P.s. I tend to keep clear of `3d` games on the amiga...I still think you can
make a good game in 2d (take foundation and age of empires). When you`ve
programmed the pc..and seen a 3d card that cost as much as my A1200 did,
manage 40,000 textured and lightsourced triangles per frame that pretty much
takes the cake. I want to do some 3d when I upgrade my amiga to ppc and gfx
card (when I can afford it that is!).




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_33" "Re: 3D Quake Clone"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Wed, 2 Dec 1998 15:12:17 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Wed, 02 Dec 1998 14:52:38 +0000
Subject: Re: 3D Quake Clone

Hi,

>> If you CANNOT make a game with that has full screen display 320x256 with
>> sound, enemies etc run at a MINIMAL of 15fps then I'm not interested
> (sorry).

> Surely that depends on the cpu?? 15fps on an 020 is a lot different to
> 15fps on an 060.

Yep, you can't do much 3D stuff with 020 in 1/4 of a second especially if
you're talking about a pure polygon based game. I'm not even sure than
Amiga Quake can get past 15fps even on 040 and there's no way you'd
ever make a game that is faster than Quake AND better looking. And if
the game isn't better looking than a 3 year old PC title who cares about
it? Obviously this comment is based around the first person shooter genre.

> is..on the pc it was ok) or even at worse you could try open gl (hmmm..not
> sure about that..it`s not amazingly fast on the pc).

Best wait for Warp3D for 3D amiga games. It'll support all 3 of the
current and future 3D graphics cards (Virge,Permida,3Dfx) and will
provide 3D in software form (PPC+68K) if no 3d card is available.

> P.s. I tend to keep clear of `3d` games on the amiga...I still think you
can
> make a good game in 2d (take foundation and age of empires).

I think the term '3D Game' is harder to define these days. You mentioned
Foundation being a 2D game but it still has three dimentions in the
traditional Isometric sense. As I develop the game further I hope to bring
in more and more traditional 3D effects like gouraud shading and
replace the fixed isometric rendering with proper 3D perspective
techniques. It's funny how 2D games can evolve into 3D with some
slight 'tweaks'.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

