@NODE "Mail_48" "Re: 3D Quake Clone"
 ([62.136.38.108] helo=sneech ident=paul)
	by mail4.svr.pol.co.uk with smtp (Exim 2.05iplimit-2 #5)
	id 0zm8PG-000166-00
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sat, 5 Dec 1998 03:29:18 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Sat, 05 Dec 1998 02:24:54 +0000
Subject: Re: 3D Quake Clone
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hi,

>> Probably just C. In my recent experiments the C language is very
>> fast and can do most things as fast as Asm unless you spend a
>> lot of time hand optimizing. =

>
>    Probably C code is fast (yes it is) BUT please don't say that it's a=
s
> fast than hand written ASM one. Even the most optimized C routine is at=

> least 3 time faster when rewritten in ASM. To be convinced, just try to=

> write a fast c2p in C langage. Try and send me the result ;=B0).

yeah but you're talking about very tiny code sections that are coded
with optimal speed and size as well as a system specific task that would
never be required on any other platform and unlikely to be required
in any common hardware form. I was talking about a huge game engine
like Quake which despite the work that went into rewriting most of
it in Asm never went anything close to 2 times faster from my own tests.
Quake in original C version was very slow, rewritten in Asm it was
just slow :)

>    On the PC, the main processor is SO fast, than the developpers doesn=
't
> take the time to optimize their routines. Why because it's useless, lik=
e
> most time consuming routine are done by external drivers (DirectX or 3D=

> cards...).

I think you'd better take a look at Amiga code written in Asm for
example Gloom, AB3D and Breathless. Then came along Doom
written for this SO fast platform by coders who are not supposed to
be bothered about optimizing. Then you see Doom has much better
performance compared to any home grown Asm effort. The same
can be said for Quake. Id are the pioneers in optimized game
programming (and also VERY portable code) so please don't claim
they don't optimize. Sure they don't code in pure Asm but as I said,
that kind of thing is just silly when you have SO much power.

> Only the main code should be optimized, which is ridiculous. But
> without 3D card, you can easely see a well optimized game and a bad
> optimized game even on P250, the optimized one will run at 40 fps
> when the second one will run at 20 fps.

I would also like to claim that using 3D cards is the way to go. Who
wants to see game programmers having to hand optimize 3d routines,
texture mapping, shading, filtering etc.. I think it's better to work on
the game itself and leave the 3D stuff to the experts (3Dfx etc.) who
can make super fast and cheap hardware.

>    May be I've old though, may be optimizing is no more important, but =
I
> think than power of new processor are wasted if the code is not optimiz=
ed.

I never said you shouldn't optimize but I do think optimized portable C
is much more clever than optimized Asm. I don't mind working in Asm
for small jobs lik c2p, p2c, chunky blitting, special gfx effects etc.. b=
ut
thats where I'd draw the line. This is why we all like to use Blitz.. we =
all
know it's not as fast as C or ASm but it's much faster an asier to develo=
p
with which means projects can get huge AND easy to keep control of.

Cheers,

-- =

