claiming that all PC coders are lazy. This just doesn't stand up when
you compare the results. Okay so some Amiga programmer decides
to take the C code written by a PC programmer and convert it to Asm.
This prooves that Asm is faster than C but the PC programmer is still
the source of the original routines and algorythms which is where
the real difference is.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >



