@NODE "Mail_85" "Re: 64 colour bitmap"
 (Eudora Internet Mail Server 2.2); Tue, 15 Dec 1998 13:35:48 +0000
Date: Tue, 15 Dec 1998 13:38:27 +0100
From: Manfred Linzner <manfred.linzner@munich.netsurf.de>
X-Accept-Language: en
Subject: Re: 64 colour bitmap
Encoding: 7bit



stocksjames wrote:
> 
> I know someone asked recently, but how do you display a 64 colour
> bitmap?
> My display (a 320*256 done in DPaint) just comes up blank!
> Slices or Coplists will do...
> 
> TIA


;*********************

BLITZ

initcoplist 0,44,256,$13006,8,64,0
bitmap 0,320,256,6:decodeilbm 0,?pic
decodepalette 0,?pal
displaybitmap 0,0
displaypalette 0,0
createdisplay 0

mousewait:end

pic
incbin "yourpictures.iff"
pal
incbin "yourpalette.iff"

;*********************


This should do in Blitzmode

