@NODE "Mail_104" "Re: amigalibs.res"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Thu, 3 Dec 1998 05:01:37 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Thu, 03 Dec 1998 04:54:04 +0000
Subject: Re: amigalibs.res

Hi,

>I`m getting really crazy! I cant seem to get operating system calls
>like windowtofront and request working. I know I could once, as I
> made programs using these commands. But now they just load in
> with ????? in place of the commands. I know I need to add some
>libs to deflibs, but I dont seem to have the neccesary libs. Please
> help me out, as I cant figure it out.

You must have compiled your deflibs without the amigalibs/
files which all look like #?.library1 or similar. I think the
WindowToFront_ function is in intuition.library1 but that not
an important factor. Also, perhaps you edited the lib number
or added a lib with a clashing lib number.

the amigalibs.res has very little to do with your problem. It's
only a set of defines, constants, newtypes etc.. Nothing to do
with the actual libs.

Cheers

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

