From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Sat, 12 Dec 1998 21:59:04 +0000
Subject: Re: Aminet Censored!? - (Maybe) Off Topic!

Hi,

>>  ->Yes, we have more than 40 Blitz files in there already - but the
>>  ->that unless there are at least 40 (or whatever the minimum is)
>>  ->files to leave behind in the basic/ directory, they won't let us
>>  ->Blitz files to a new directory...

>>  OK, everyone, let's all write one AmigaBASIC example code and upload it
>>  into the dev/basic directory =]

> So you want your Own Blitz Directory on Aminet ? I'll tell you what why
> don't you write about 40 Programs or Demo Code for Blitz Basic and Then
> Upload it . Hey Presto ! Now you have got a Blitz Dircetory on Aminet :)

No, Aminet won't allow it. If a Blitz dir is created the current blitz files
will need to be moved into it. This would reduce the number of non-blitz
related files to less than 40 and so the argument is that Blitz dominates
the dev/basic so much, there's no need for a new home. So, if someone
uploaded some *usefull* non-blitz related files there would then be a
good reason to give blitz it's own dir.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

