From: Paul Burkey <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Sun, 13 Dec 1998 01:12:05 +0000
Subject: Re: Aminet Censored!? - (Maybe) Off Topic!

Hi,

>>> My point is something which could very easly die off soon has a draw
>>> on Aminet whilsed where it all happing dosn't.  Make sence dosn't it,
>>> NOT!
>> 
>> Are you saying Aminet affects the amount of users who are active on
>> mailig lists depending on the existance of a subdirectory? :) I think
>> amos users are dying off because it has its roots set in the distant ECS
>> past. While Blitz was at least linked with Amigas distant AGA past ;)

> Blitz isn't default to any chip set.  I could open screens for any
> chip set thay every come out.  Most blitz programes are going more
> so called O/S freindly ways. I hear lot less about Blitz mode then did
> say 8 mounths ago.  

Yeah but to make games that are so called O/S friendly you usually
have to avoid Blitz altogether and use graphics.library calls. When
you create bitmaps and use the bulk of blitz's graphics functions
you will be using the hardware direct. So, as I said, it's linked
with AGA (and ECS too). So more and more we'll be using Blitz's
amazing shared library support. I suppose thats still Blitz isn't it! :)

> And what a lode of rubbish about total files
> left in draw a less 40.  Wait for it, soon it will be 100 files.

Well if Aminet was split into small directories containing highly specific
groups of less than 40 files there's be over 1,400 directories. So there
have to be some rules. Even 100 files is quite small compared to most
other directories.

> Is Foundation realy worth having or is Setters2 better?

Dunno, it depends what kind of game you want to play. It's a bit
like asking whats worth having, Tomb Raider III or Quake 2? I'd
probably have both and enjoy them in equal amounts for different
reasons. I suppose it depends what you're after.

I suppose it also depends how good the Amiga version of Settlers 2
is. I'm a bit worried about the fact that Titan have to write their own
engine for it since they were only provided with the gfx and sound
data for the game and not the source code. I hope they manage to
reach the quality of the BlueByte version!

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >



@ENDNODE
