On 12-Dec-98, Andrew wrote:

> Blitz isn't default to any chip set.  I could open screens for any
> chip set thay every come out.  Most blitz programes are going more
> so called O/S freindly ways. I hear lot less about Blitz mode then did
> say 8 mounths ago.   And what a lode of rubbish about total files
> left in draw a less 40.  Wait for it, soon it will be 100 files.

Well, the Blitz mode has nothing to do with any specific chipsets, nor is=
 it
particularily OS unfriendly. It just that people use this interesting way=

of addressing the AMiGA's hardware without REALLY knowing what they're
doing, (Which is not surprising at all, since AMiGA NEVER printed an AGA
specific HRM). So most people decide to use Intuition screens, not becase=

they're nessecarilly better, but because there is much less hassle.

> Is Foundation realy worth having or is Setters2 better?

An interesting question. Having not played much Foundation, and only seen=

Settlers 2 on a PC, I'd be inclined to say "Get foundation", not just
because I think Paul Burkey's huge work should be rewarded, but because t=
he
game is HERE, NOW. When settlers 2 finally DOES come out for the AMiGA,
(sometime last quarter of next year, if we're lucky) the PC public will
have much cooler games to play. Also, From what I've played, settlers  is=

not SIGNIFICANTLY a better game than the original settlers (Which was an
AMiGA first :o), and BlueBytes last :o( ) so I don't think I'll be gettin=
g
Settlers 2, the game is just too tedious. I still might get foundation, i=
f
the updates really are as good as paul says :o)


Regards
-- =

