Hi Everybody,

On 30-Nov-98, David Mcminn wrote:
> On 30 Nov 98, at 7:07, Curt Esser wrote:
> 
>>  Yes, we have more than 40 Blitz files in there already - but the
problem
>>  is that unless there are at least 40 (or whatever the minimum is)
>>  NON-BLITZ files to leave behind in the basic/ directory, they won't let
>>  us move the Blitz files to a new directory... > > I'm nearly finishing
>>  version 2 (several improvements and inovations) but i > fear that when
i
>>  upload it, they won't make it available!
> 
> As far as I can see, there are 35 non-blitz archive in that drawer. 
> I propose that everyone who ever done anything in AmigaBASIC/<some 
> other basic> to upload what you've got now. Otherwise someones gonna 
> have to take up AmigaBASIC for a day to create 5 things to upload.

Well, that might work.  The last time, we did have 40 Blitz files (new
ones)
ready to upload to the new directory, in addition to the Blitz files that
were already in dev/basic.  But Urban Mueller turned down our (OK, I
started the whole thing last time, I'll take the blame) MY request for the
new directory because he wouldn't shut down the old directory, and he
wouldn't keep a directory with less than 40 files in it.

So if someone wants to make sure there are at least 40 non-Blitz files in
dev/basic, maybe it's time to try again.

Here is the actual info text from Aminet:


<sb>
If you have 40 files of one type, you can request a separate directory
on Aminet. In that case we need the following info:

1. Suggest a name, like pix/shoe, where the 2nd part is 5 letters max.
2. Suggest a description, about 20 letters. See pub/aminet/TREE
3. If there are files already on Aminet that should be moved to the
   new directory, send us their lines from INDEX. This is a must if
   there are files that should be moved there.
   I MEAN IT! WE WANT THE LINES FROM THE INDEX FILE AND NOTHING ELSE!
   ASCII! UNEDITED! UNINDENTED!
4. In the same mail, tell us how many files you plan to upload for that
   directory, if any.

Send your application to umueller@aminet.org . Then you'll get our OK 
(or the denial). If no files have to be moved, we will create the 
directory as soon as a significant number of uploads for it arrive. 
Put the new directory name in the Type: field of your readmes.

  -Urban


<sb>




                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




