@NODE "Mail_124" "AminetBlitzDirectory"
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby.lnk@ispi.net>
Date: Sat, 12 Dec 1998 17:01:41 +0500
Subject: AminetBlitzDirectory

Hi all,

  Many people have indicated that they would like to see a seperate
sub-directory for Blitz Basic on Aminet, and I also would like that.
As a number of people liked my idea to upload some of my best Amiga
Basic software to the Aminet, thus making it possible for Blitz to
split off into its own directory, I am going to do it.  Sorry I am
so slow, but it is taking some time to find the latest versions of
all my old software and decide which ones to put on.  I don't want
to clutter up Aminet with junk,so I am trying to make sure that
everything I put on works well and is potentially useful to any who
may still be using hardware and O.S.s capable of running Amiga Basic
applications.  I also have to make read-me files for all of them
and figure out how to upload to Aminet as I have never done it.
(Any help here would be appreciated)
  As soon as this is all accomplished I will message this list and
we can make a request for the seperate Blitz directory.

 cacha later,

Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)




@ENDNODE
