--BOUNDARY.1747582216.2

Hi,

> all my old software and decide which ones to put on.  I don't want
> to clutter up Aminet with junk,so I am trying to make sure that
> everything I put on works well and is potentially useful to any who
> may still be using hardware and O.S.s capable of running Amiga Basic
> applications.  I also have to make read-me files for all of them
> and figure out how to upload to Aminet as I have never done it.
> (Any help here would be appreciated)

Do you know the format of the read-me or you just need to
know about uploading? Here's a simple example readme just
in case and maybe it'll help anyone else who needs help.

Short:    (insert short description {40 chars or less} here..)
Author:   (insert author name and/or email)
Uploader: (insert your name and/or email)
Type:     (insert path here eg, dev/basic)
<insert blank line.....>
<now insert a longer description (few lines or pages) if you want>

remember the readme and the archive must be exactly the same
and use "<14 char max>.lha" and "<14 char max>.readme" names.

Then upload *both files* to one of the big Aminet sites such as
"ftp.wustl.edu" or "ftp.uni-paderborn.de". You must upload the
files into the /new/ directory which is found in the root of aminet.
In the washington site its /systems/amiga/aminet/new and in
the paderborn site its /ftp/aminet/pub/new

the exact upload info is found in an uploads readme which
is found in the root of main aminet sites.

> As soon as this is all accomplished I will message this list and
> we can make a request for the seperate Blitz directory.

Okay, we'll need a list of the current Blitz files in the dev/basic
directory that require moving. I've counted most of them in the
attached list which is almost complete. BTW, when i removed
these entries (117 blitz files) from my aminet index it left me with
well over 40 non-blitz entries! Anyway, there's nothing wrong
with uploading more stuff because the bigger and the more mixed
the dev/basic dir gets, the more reason for splitting it up! To
be honest, I think we'd better have at least 60 non-blitz files
before we pester Urban *yet again*.

There's already over 170 archives adding up to more than 17meg
of files although this isn't anywhere near as big as the dev/amos
or the dev/e directories which contain 33meg (250-280 files)
each. So, maybe we need to collect up some usefull blitz stuff? I
think if we did have a dev/blitz directory there'd be more incentive
to support it with usefull files. Perhaps this explains the size of
the Amos and E presence on aminet.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

