@NODE "Mail_140" "Re: Blitz CPU routine for arcade game"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sun, 27 Dec 1998 12:46:34 +0000
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 27 Dec 98 12:43:33 +0000
Subject: Re: Blitz CPU routine for arcade game
Encoding: 7bit

Mr Lokke,

> See I once suggested this, and was told not to use RTGMaster (I presume)
> because some people couldn't get it to work. Besides for AGA screens at
> least Milded is faster. And graphics board support ? Gheez, I just don't
> know. I havn't got one myself, but a friend says the graphics look wierd
> (Like as if the Graphicscard THOUGHT is was displaying a planar buffer, but
> was in reality show a chunky one) which look rather psycadelic.

A simple call to WritePixelArray8_, a loop of WritePixelLine8_'s, or
the untokenised WriteChunkyPixels_ is all you need to send the chunky
data [of mildred] to a graphics-card display.

-- 
Paul.

