@NODE "Mail_151" "Blitz Source Check"
 ([62.136.34.90] helo=sneech ident=paul)
	by mail5.svr.pol.co.uk with smtp (Exim 2.05iplimit-2 #5)
	id 0zm028-0004g2-00
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Fri, 4 Dec 1998 18:32:52 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Fri, 04 Dec 1998 16:18:06 +0000
Subject: Blitz Source Check

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1743348312.1

Hi,

After my last post regardig rogue error messages I decided to start
working on a little project I have planned for a while. The purpose
of this project is to fill in where the Blitz compiler lacks features. The
compiler is very old now and most modern Amiga C compilers can
give error messages that make Blitz look archaic! When using
a modern compiler you get messages that aren't always that
important but they can help when cleaning up your code. For
example, wouln't it be nice if Blitz told you when you'd SHARED
a variable but never actually used it? Perhaps you used
End Statement when you should have used End Function. Perhaps
you'd assigned a variable eg, age.b=0 but then never actually
used it. These are just some of the basic things that C compilers
do as standard.

This is why I plan to make a parser to check for all the 'little things'
that are missed by the Blitz compiler itself. I just spent an hour
doing the basic Statement/Function/End Statement/End Function
checking and it found 8 errors in my Foundation source :) This
isn't surprizing when I have 266 functions and 20,000 lines of
code! But the important thing is, Blitz should have tracked these
problems down for me! grrr.

Anyway, I hope to add the check for rogue SHARED variables
and the 'initialized but unused' variables next but I'm a little
busy atm so I thought I'd gather some other suggestions for now.

The attached example will require ascii source file and will check
for End Statement/End Function errors.

Cheers

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

--BOUNDARY.1743348312.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="BlitzSourceCheck.lha"
Encoding: base64


--BOUNDARY.1743348312.1--




@ENDNODE
