Hi,

> Anyway, the error it reports is:
> "See if obsolete *Ours;blahblahblah..."
> Maybe it's because of the comment on the same line?

Yes it was! The checker didn't strip out the comments so it thought
the ;blahblahblah bit was part of the variable itself! No wonder it
thought you'd not used it :) Anyway, I've updated the program so
it now strips out comments before making the checks. I also fixed
a known problem in the unused functions check.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

