I'm quite happy with SuperTEDv2.52 but i guess it could do with
an update. Perhaps RWE are willing to pass on the job? I don't
know if it's viable to make a new editor when thre's already a half
decent on available.

> TED is a slight big old in itself..

but SuperTED is only 2 years old. Thats not too bas since the language
itself hasn't changed at all.

> and I dunno if it'd be possible or not,
> to create another editor to replace it.. but I do know it'd be nice..
> something that handled a lot like Cygnus Ed.. where if you hit return on a
> line it would linefeed THAT line, not the line below..

In this case it would be better for someone to develop a cli blitz
compiler like the one RWE (Steve Matty at least) were talking about
just over a year ago. That would let you use ANY editor. I don't
think it's wise to start a new editor from scratch.

> Since Ted is nothing like a standard text editor or wordprocessor.. it
> makes it difficult to make the transition to other programs.. .. and let's
> face it.. TEd is a rough passover from 1.3 .. THAT.. is bad..

Ted is quite nice on my 1600x1200 graphics card screen :)

Cheers,

