Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 22 Dec 1998 09:38:56 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Blitz Source Check

On 21 Dec 98, at 18:54, Flatulator wrote:

> And the name of that compiler izzzz...?
> 
> 
> I don't know what file to download.

 I got it yesterday, I think it was bc.lha. Its not actually a command lin=
e 
compiler, what it does is this:

   Runs Blitz2
   Uses a hack to: simulate the first gadget being clicked on, the load fi=
le 
menu item being picked, enters the filename in the requester, waits for a 
specified time (note - just waits, doesn't check if file is loaded or not)=
, the 
selection of the compiler->run or compiler->create executable menu items.

 HackFest'95 thats what it is, but its such a damn cool sneaky way of doin=
g 
things. I haven't tried it yet, though.


