> sure that there is an error you could send some short source code to
> me to help fix the bug.


I had to send this to the list, for some reason your "reply-to" is the
Blitz-list.

It's just a little check to see if my program is running already, so I can
exit.

And before anyone says I'm evil because I won't let people run 2 copies at
once, the program uses it's own PUBLIC screen, and there can't be 2 with
the same name...

Anyway, the error it reports is:

"See if obsolete *Ours;blahblahblah..."

Maybe it's because of the comment on the same line?

Here is the source
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1747970920.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="example.asc"

;-----------------------------------

Function.b ScreenThere{}    ;see if our screen is open
SHARED *Ours                ;pointer to screen structure

  *Ours = LockPubScreen_("BeatBox2")
  void=UnlockPubScreen_(0,*Ours)
  If *Ours
    Function Return True
  Else
    Function Return False
  EndIf
End Function

;----------------------------------------------------

scpnt.b = ScreenThere{}            ;see if we're already running
If scpnt = True                    ;YES!
  ScreenToFront_(*Ours)            ;so pop our screen to the front
  End                              ;and we are history
EndIf


--BOUNDARY.1747970920.2--




@ENDNODE
