Well, I'm sure this isn't the right way to do it, but it works.

I send my screen to the back, then make sure my pointer is in a "safe" place
(not over any of my gadgets, etc) using the AbsMouse command, then use the
ClickButton command to activate the WB screen...

Yeah, I know it's a hack, but I haven't found any other way to do it.


