@NODE "Mail_180" "C Include files / File ID library"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    20 Dec 98 17:32:03 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Sun, 20 Dec 1998 17:31:43 -0000
Subject: C Include files / File ID library


--Message-Boundary-26355
encoding: Quoted-printable
Content-description: Mail message body

Hi James,

 I don't know about an automatic generator for C include files, but heres =
the 
FileID.library ones. There is two changes from the C includes:

    the constant FID_SCREAM3MOD is changed to #FID_SCREAM3_MOD due to 
tokenising problems

    the library name can be accessed using the macro !FILEIDNAME, i.e. 
OpenLibrary_(!FILEIDNAME,37) (not that you'd ever need to call OL_ on it).

 As for making it into a resident, you need to have amigalibsii.res reside=
nt to 
use it (it has a couple of things from that in the newtypes), so if you in=
clude 
that and make a resident, you end up with a file which has all the 
amigalibsii.res stuff in it as well. Perhaps if you just include the sourc=
e 
(file) in your code near the top somewhere, and have amigalibsii.res in th=
e 
resident options.

 I apologise for not having time to try it, but I'm taking a quick break f=
rom 
XMas shopping (hell) before I go to work (more hell). Call me all the name=
s 
under the sun if it doesn't work, then tell me about it.


