Wow, thanks - that was quick!

I might even try and make a generic converter myself since I can compare
this directly with the C includes...

> Perhaps if you just
> include the source (file) in your code near the top somewhere, and have=

> amigalibsii.res in the resident options.

Yes, this is what I've done...

> Call me all the names under the sun if it doesn't work, then tell me ab=
out it.

Hey, don't tempt me ;)

Well, I tried to make a little test using the library, but it always
fails with "GURU - illegal instruction" on the FIAllocFileInfo_ command.

Any idea why? I've attached my attempt, which obviously needs the include=
s
stuck in above it...I also wasn't sure if FIAllocFileInfo_ needed the
brackets after it, but it fails either way...

I think if I can get past this, I'll be OK...then I'll knock together
some functions and put a little Blitz FID package together...

Any help appreciated :)

Oh, yeah, I'd better point out that I do have FileID.library installed ;)=


See ya,
-- =

James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
Team *AMIGA*, member of *Dogbert's New Ruling Class.*
Connected from Dundee, Scotland...

--BOUNDARY.1748156752.3
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="FIAllocFileInfo.asc"
Content-Description: Any ideas?


; attempted FIAllocFileInfo_ thing...

*FileInfo.FI_FileInfo=FIAllocFileInfo_() ; FIAllocFileInfo (void)

; The above line causes "GURU!!! Illegal instruction!",
; both with or without the brackets at the end...

If *FileInfo
  FIFreeFileInfo_ *FileInfo            ; FIFreeFileInfo (FileInfo)
EndIf

End


