Hi there,

> I might even try and make a generic converter myself since I can compare
> this directly with the C includes...

 OK, that would be cool. You just need to remember that in C, both constan=
ts 
and macros are defined using #define, sometimes its not always apparent wh=
at 
they should be (unless you have a clever automatic converter). One way to 
circumvent this is to use Blitz macros for all #defines, which is essentia=
lly 
what happens in C (all #defines are directly replaced at compile time, whi=
ch is 
what macros are).
 
> Well, I tried to make a little test using the library, but it always
> fails with "GURU - illegal instruction" on the FIAllocFileInfo_ command.
> 
> Any idea why? I've attached my attempt, which obviously needs the includ=
es
> stuck in above it...I also wasn't sure if FIAllocFileInfo_ needed the
> brackets after it, but it fails either way...
> 
> I think if I can get past this, I'll be OK...then I'll knock together so=
me
> functions and put a little Blitz FID package together...
> 
> Any help appreciated :)
> 
> Oh, yeah, I'd better point out that I do have FileID.library installed ;=
)

 I tried your test prog, and it worked fine here [no brackets]. Possibly y=
ou've 
used an existing library number when you fdconverted? I'll try it at home =
as 
well, as Blitz/WinUAE/LESDebugger is not a good combination.

 
