On 21 Dec 98, at 19:59, James L Boyd wrote:

> No, I've just re-installed the (fd'd) library, and it still doesn't work=
.
> The commands tokenise too, so it seems weird. And the test programs in t=
he
> FIDLIB80.lha archive work, so the fileid.library is fine on my system...
> 
> What number do you have the blitz library set to?

213. Generally, I've put system libraries starting around 255 and going do=
wn.
 
> And could you please post me the full source you're compiling? This 
> is weird...

 Much the same as your source (if not identical):

XINCLUDE "blitzlibs:fid_incs.bb2"
*MyFileInfo.FI_FileInfo =3D FIAllocFileInfo_
If *MyFileInfo <> 0
    FIFreeFileInfo_ *MyFileInfo
End If
End

In compiler options I use the default settings, and also "Make Smallest" t=
urned 
