@NODE "Mail_193" "Re: Colour Fonts"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 09 Dec 1998 20:53:25 -0500
Subject: Re: Colour Fonts

Hi Daniel,

On 09-Dec-98, Daniel Allsopp wrote:
> Hi all,
> 
> Does anyone know how to use two colour fonts at the same time each with
> their own palette. I've got two 8 colour fonts which I want to use on the
> window at the same time. Any ideas?

You could convert one to a 16 colour font, using only the last 8 colours.

Then set your palette colours # 0 - 15 to correspond to the fonts colours.

(assuming your screen has 16 or more colours?)
> 
> Also, does the palette information for the colour fonts have to start at
0
> in the palette?

I think it does, since colourfonts are really a series of "brushes" or
"shapes".

But just like a brush, you don't have to actually USE every colour.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
