@NODE "Mail_197" "Re: Continuing problem with Freq!"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 21 Dec 1998 17:09:35 -0500
Subject: Re: Continuing problem with Freq!

Hi Peter

On 21-Dec-98, Peter Nightingale wrote:
> Hi..
> In the following bit of code, (taken from a larger program) the first
`Freq
> 8,blah` works perfectly, and the second (at the bottom) stops the sample
> playing on channel 2. This is driving me insane! Does anybody have any
idea
> why? BTW thanks to Curt Esser for the source of his similar (working)
> program.

> S.f=sweepf.f
> steps.f=(fre.f-sweepf.f)/(sweept.f*60)
> Freq 8,#k/(107*(S.f-0.1))

^^^^^^^ You might want to check to see if some bad value is being given to
the command here (like a negative number, or 0 or something?)

Also, I'm not sure, but I would guess that the frequency value should be
given as a word or a long.  As usual, the documentation for the command is
rather vague...

But worth a try, anyway...

Later...
-- 
