@NODE "Mail_198" "Converting C Includes"
 ([62.136.14.85] helo=all-hail.freeserve.co.uk ident=James L Boyd)
	by mail11.svr.pol.co.uk with smtp (Exim 2.054 #1)
	id 0zrkA1-0002EM-00
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sun, 20 Dec 1998 14:48:45 +0000
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 20 Dec 1998 14:43:47 +0000
Subject: Converting C Includes

Hi all,

Does anybody have a program to convert C includes to Blitz?

I seem to remember somebody last year or earlier this year starting
something like this.

Would anybody be willing to write one? I'm not clever enough for this ;)

And failing that, would anybody be willing to convert the includes
from the FileID.library? I can post them, or the archive itself...

This library would be an amazing addition to Blitz, giving us the 
power to inspect a file before performing any operation on it,
to see what it is...fileid.library recognises several hundred
filetypes, and would be useful to many people here I think...

Of course, a general converter would be the best solution...

Anybody?

See ya,

-- 
