On 26-Dec-98, Anthony Sherratt wrote:

> How do you sort out the palettes when you use =

> Coplists and DualPlayfields ?

> I seem to have set them up right but as far as I can
> see both bitmaps (ex. DisplayBitmap 1,2) use the first
> 16 colours ?!?

Well, AGA has 8 bitplanes, which means that you can show two 4 bit deep
bitmaps. This should give you two 16 colour bitmaps. However, how they ar=
e
Used in Blitz, I do not know. Most logically it would be to use the first=

16, and the last 16 colours. But I'm not sure.

> At the moment im using... =

>  CopList 0,44,208,$13438,8,32,0

> Dunno what im doing wrong, any exmples you people
> have would help, thanks :)

Anyways, I would like you to reconsider writeing your game in a more syst=
em
friendly manner, if at all possible. This way all people at least have a
chance to decide wheter the game is good or not, and won't get annoyed th=
at
they can't play your games. (In the same way I am annoyed at AMOS for
having to use the copperscreen, so I cannot play the two good games ever
done in AMOS.


Regards
