@NODE "Mail_211" "Re: CPU Usage,...."
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Tue, 8 Dec 1998 20:52:26 +0000
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@velvety.demon.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 08 Dec 1998 20:43:02 +0000
Subject: Re: CPU Usage,....

Loki churned out *this* drivel :

>   Anybody know how I can "simply" measure CPU usage (Load)?,. Say as a
> percentage?

I don't think there is any simple way.

You could get the Executive 2.10 archive from Aminet - there's a drawer
called "data" in there, in which you'll find another archive called 
"Developers.lha". This contains an API interface to Executive, as well
as a /shared library which works without Executive/ (AFAIK), called 
sysinfo.library (no relation to the SysInfo program).

This library has CPU usage functions in it, among other things.

All the autodocs, includes, etc are there...just gotta fdconvert it...

That's the best I can offer :)

...Just had a closer look - looks pretty complicated! Rather you than me ;)

See ya,
-- 
James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
