>> deflibs?

>Hehe, your programs NEED deflibs do they ? Well, mon ami, you have an OL=
D
>version of of Blitz. I specifically said version > 1.9. And these versio=
ns
>of Blitz will simply load all the files your Deflibs file USUALLY contai=
ns.
>If your Blitz is configured properly. And I'm sure I'm not to blame for =
the
>short commings of viewlibs.bb, If I need to know which libs I have, I ju=
st
>do a "dir Blitz2:Userlibs/ ALL" from my shell. And mine works fine.
>Ofcourse my Blitz is also correctly installed.

Ok, I have version 2.1 of Blitz (never had an older one) and here is an e=
xtract of the 'Release Notes' documentation:

=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D

4. Library handling
-------------------

BlitzBASIC commands are loaded by the program from several sources:

acidlibs - a single file containing standard Blitz commands
deflibs  - commands compiled from third party libs found in blitzlibs:
userlibs - all libs found in directories branching off blitz2:userlibs

The reason for this change is to make it easier for Acid Software to
distribute libs in the future. Users who build up a collection of third
party libraries in their deflibs file will be able to upgrade their
acidlibs without reconstructing their entire blitzlibs: volume.

Those developers creating their own libraries can now use the userlibs
drawer to hold beta versions of their compiled libs allowing for much
faster reloading of libs during development.

=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D

Also the papery manual says 'deflibs' is necessary on a couple of pages. =
So I made an experiment: I copied all the content of 'blitzlibs:' to the =
'Userlibs' directory, deleted (renamed!!!) the 'deflibs' file and the 'bl=
itzlibs' directory, run Blitz and loaded my sources. All worked well (no =
????? commands). Probably you don't need 'deflibs' because you have all t=
he third party libs in 'Userlibs' (if version 1.9 did have one). But, as =
the documentation says, this directory should only be used 'during develo=
pment'. Moreover I think that a compiled file like 'deflibs' is faster to=
 be loaded.

I think that's all.



-- =

Best regards,

Luca.

