Hello Thomas.

On 25-Dec-98, Thomas Newsom wrote:

>>> I recently bought a 2nd hand copy of the Blitz Support Suite, install=
ed
>> it
>>> and now sod all works!

>>> All my extra libs tokens all appear as "??????" in my code and all
>> examples
>>> :(

>>> Help!

>>  Sure. It is most likely bacause the BSS installer did something wrong=

>>  with your deflibs file, try remakeing Deflibs, or removing iit all
>>  together. In both cases, make sure you have all the right libs in all=

the
>>  right places. (And I once thought DevPac 3 was a hassle, gheez) :o)

> I removed deflibs, same problem. I recompiled deflibs, same problem. Al=
l
> libs are in the right place, same problem.

> Any more ideas?

Well it IS because Blitz doesn't load in the libraries. That's the only
reason something won't tokenise (AFAIK). So, try removing the deflibs fil=
e,
and use snoopdos to find out what fails. Other than that I suggest remove=

everything, and start over. But this is a bit drastic, and rather uncalle=
d
for since the problem is failure to load libraries. Maybe they aren't the=
re
anymore ?


Regards
