-Mehiz



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_235" "Re: Doing the token thing :)"
From: Mika Jussila <krf@saunalahti.fi>
Date: Sat, 07 Jan 1978 09:19:50 +0200
Organization: the krafted syndikate!
Subject: Re: Doing the token thing :)

Eeeks!
This is a duplicate yes but the first one left with a rather confusing subject
Sorry about that...

Reply to a message from Curt Esser (07-Dec-98):

>On 06-Jan-78, Mika Jussila wrote:
>> Could any of you ppl tell me how I could parse a tokenised blitz source
>to
>> standard ASCII and vice-versa?
>> An example would do if you have one...

>Actually, no example needed - just load the tokenized source into Blitz,
>then select "Save ASCII" on the menu.  To re-tokenize an ascii source, the
>same thing - load it into Blitz, then save it out again with the regular
>"Save As" menu item.

>Note:  I'm not sure if the standard Blitz Ted editor has a "Save ASCII"
>option on the menu - if not, get the SuperTed editor from
>Aminet/dev/basic/

Erm... What I meant to ask is if I could do this tokenizing and de-tokenizing
inside my
program so i would be able to make a program which could save and load blitz
sources either as ascii or in the blitz tokenized format (and convert between
them).

-- 
*** - Mika "Mehiz" Jussila / G-Men Projects & krafted innovations!



