@NODE "Mail_236" "DoubleBuffering"
From: Daniel Allsopp <daniel@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk>
	Blitz Basic List <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Tue, 15 Dec 1998 18:15:35 +0000
Subject: DoubleBuffering

Hi ,

I found the following code in Curt Essers tips guide, which is used for
DoubleBuffering a cybergraphX screen using top and bottom parts of a
screen/window.

cgx_width=320
cgx_height=240
the windows height is 480.

Statement CyberDbSwitch{}
    SHARED cgx_width,cgx_height

    *vp.ViewPort=ViewPort(1)
    rast.w=*vp\RasInfo\RyOffset

    If rast=0
      rast=cgx_height
    Else
      rast=0
    End If

    *vp\RasInfo\RyOffset=rast
    WaitBOVP_(*vp)
    ScrollVPort_(*vp)
End Statement

The RasInfo isn't a part of the ViewPort (libs 1) or _ViewPort (libs 2)
Newtype.

Now seens as this doesn't work I wrote a similar one where the newtype
information can be found. It's different in the AmigaLibs.res and
AmigalibsII.res The viewport and rastport newtypes have underscores before
their names, but still don't hold the RasInfo type inside.

Anyway I came up with this, but it crashes ;(

  Statement CyberDbSwitch{}
    SHARED cgx_width,cgx_height

    *vp.RasInfo=ViewPort(1)
    rast.w=*vp\RyOffset

    If rast=0
      rast=cgx_height
    Else
      rast=0
    End If

    *vp\RyOffset=rast
    WaitBOVP_(*vp)
    ScrollVPort_(*vp)
  End Statement


Any ideas on how to fix it??

-- 
Cheers,
    Daniel

<tsb>E-Mail: daniel@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk
<tsb>URL: http://www.thesnakepit.demon.co.uk/
<tsb>



@ENDNODE
