@NODE "Mail_239" "Enigma."
          Mon, 14 Dec 1998 13:37:24 +0000
          14 Dec 98 13:37:25 +0000
From: "S.J.CROY" <ap6013@qmw.ac.uk>
Organization: University of London (QMW)
Date: Mon, 14 Dec 1998 13:37:09 +0000
encoding: 7BIT
Subject: Enigma.


Hello Blitzers.

	I came up with this interesting "happening" at the weekend. 
On my system, opening any screen has caused it to have a grey 
line on the left side, and when setting the border to black this 
becomes VERY noticable.  I had done everything I know off to get 
rid of this but nothing worked and I gave up on it.

	BUT at the weekend I opened a screen using the NLibs 
from Fred, set the background colour to black and guess what? 
Yep no grey line on the left side!! I couldn`t believe it! Does anyone 
have any info on this or any reson why Fred`s libs are that bit 
different?  I can set this screen as public/ Multiscan anything and 
the grey line refuses to appear

Help me please
Steven


@ENDNODE
