@NODE "Mail_241" "Re: Enigma."
 (Eudora Internet Mail Server 2.2); Mon, 14 Dec 1998 15:12:03 +0000
Date: Mon, 14 Dec 1998 15:14:44 +0100
From: Manfred Linzner <manfred.linzner@munich.netsurf.de>
X-Accept-Language: en
Subject: Re: Enigma.
Encoding: 8bit



"S.J.CROY" wrote:
> 
> Hello Blitzers.
> 
>         I came up with this interesting "happening" at the weekend.
> On my system, opening any screen has caused it to have a grey
> line on the left side, and when setting the border to black this
> becomes VERY noticable.  I had done everything I know off to get
> rid of this but nothing worked and I gave up on it.
> 
>         BUT at the weekend I opened a screen using the NLibs
> from Fred, set the background colour to black and guess what?
> Yep no grey line on the left side!! I couldn`t believe it! Does anyone
> have any info on this or any reson why Fred`s libs are that bit
> different?  I can set this screen as public/ Multiscan anything and
> the grey line refuses to appear
> 
> Help me please
> Steven

if you have an AGA amiga the reason could be quite obvious. You┤ve
set border-blank (with a utility). Fine. But if colour 0 of your current
screen isnt black then you have a very tiny line on the left side. Thats
a hardware bug. Probably Fred sets colour 0 to black? The grey colour
comes from the standard WB palette i guess.

Solution: Set Colour 0 to Black (must not your background color)

-- 
