> ACID use the OpenScreen function which need to have a tons of parameters=
.
> ScreenTag is easier.

The advice Manfred gave was spot on.  What I was doing in my 
program was setting colour zero to black as well so that`s how 
come I never seen the grey line.  Any way to fix it in workbench 
goto prefs/palette and swap the grey//black colours.  You`ll notice 
that all windows are black now.  To fix them back to their original 
grey colour you need to use VisualIPrefs (the sone that lets you 
alter borderwidths, titlebar heights, close gadgets etc) to set up the 
colours.

Thanks a lot for the help
Steven




@ENDNODE
