Hello Blitzers,

Yes there is a bug with Gadget numbers. And the bug is in Gadtools for OS=
2.0, but fixed in OS3.0.
And it's hard to point. It appears when your Gadget is for example at lin=
e two and the Gadget's  number is 1(bug in pointers ?). Note that if you =
define your GadList after all other drawings, everything is fine ... very=
 strange ... but real !
So just use numbers above 50 (don't ask me why, I simply don't know) to a=
void problems. That's not hard work.

