@NODE "Mail_271" "Getting rid of files."
Date: Mon, 07 Dec 1998 11:27:35 +0000
From: stocksjames <stocksjames@KNOCK.co.uk>
Organization: Our Lady & St. Patrick's College, Knock
Subject: Getting rid of files.
Encoding: 7bit

After I've run my program a few times, it 'dies' (a run time error is
caught) when trying to open a file. When I open a file I always:

If Readfile(0,"lvl$")
	FileInput 0
	~~~~~~~~
	~~~~~~~~
	~~~~~~~~
	Closefile 0
Endif

And I always call it file '0'- there is only ever one file open.
The following seem to help:
	creating and running an executable;
	increasing object memory 150%, when prompted to;
	changing the number of files (under 'compiler options'), even if
decreasing the number of files;
	leaving the computer off for a bit;
	going straight to Blitz (I usually mess in Octamed for a bit when I sit
down);

It's as if I'm using too many files, but I can't see how this is when I
only use one and close it immediatly!

T.I.A.
	James


--

This message comes from an account holder of
Our Lady & St. Patrick's College, Knock
http://www.knock.co.uk


@ENDNODE
