@NODE "Mail_281" "Re: GFX Cards"
From: Mikkel =?iso-8859-1?Q?L=F8kke?= <FlameDuck@usa.net>
Date: Sun, 27 Dec 1998 06:13:36 +0200
Organization: A97
Subject: Re: GFX Cards
Encoding: quoted-printable
X-Info: mailto:sf@xxl.ots.dk in case of problems!

On 26-Dec-98, Andrew wrote:

> Yep I have just got my new GFX card and now i'll what to make my
> programes to us it.

Hehe, good luck :o)

> I would like to use a commaned like *ASLScreenRequest* but I can't not
> work out how to extract the details from it.

Erm, it's (allmost ?) in the manual, (or at least mine, which has the fir=
st
five issues of BUM attached to it) failing this try hitting Right Amiga +=

Help.

> All want to know is how I get the data from it so I can save pref's
> file so it is default settings for that program.

Erm it's in that example..... However the example doesn't clarify how to
exclude certain undesirable screenmodes, but there is a rather good examp=
le
on Aminet (I'm told). Unfortunately the source is in Blitz Token format (=
as
opposed to the far superior ASCII) and the author has (naturally) used
non-standard commands, which means the tokenisation is totally wrong. :o(=

(At least on my system, if anyone has the mentioned example, I would like=

to recieve a copy [in ASCII, obviously], it's the one called
"GetScreenMode.lha".)

> How would I use this information to open screen using those setting
> with GFX card.

Ah, well just inculde them in your Screen taglist and use ScreenTags to o=
pen
the screen. Erm, or you could use OS functions, naturally.

Anyway, I'm glad people are starting to make more "compatible" software,
instead of just taking the easy way out. Thanks :o)


Regards
-- =

