Hi Mikkel

On 26-Dec-98, Mikkel L=F8kke wrote:
> but there is a rather good example
> on Aminet (I'm told). Unfortunately the source is in Blitz Token format=

(as
> opposed to the far superior ASCII) and the author has (naturally) used
> non-standard commands, which means the tokenisation is totally wrong. :=
o(
> (At least on my system, if anyone has the mentioned example, I would li=
ke
> to recieve a copy [in ASCII, obviously], it's the one called
> "GetScreenMode.lha".)

I made an example (in ASCII) of using the ASL Screen Mode Requester throu=
gh
the OS rather than using the Blitz command.

So you can limit sizes, have a depth gadget (or not), show or not show
"properties" window, etc...

It also shows how to open the Screen, using a taglist made from the
information returned by the requester.

You can find it on my web page.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




