@NODE "Mail_289" "Re: GFXCard Blitting"
 ([62.136.35.157] helo=sneech ident=paul)
	by mail1.svr.pol.co.uk with smtp (Exim 2.05iplimit-2 #5)
	id 0zlkkg-00039g-00
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Fri, 4 Dec 1998 02:13:50 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Thu, 03 Dec 1998 23:56:35 +0000
Subject: Re: GFXCard Blitting

Hi,

> Which command do I need to use for buffer blitting on a screen, that shall
> also woek with gfx cards? Does BBlit and Unbuffer work with gfx cards?

No, you must understan hat BBlit/Unbuffer is  feature of Blitz and
not something that is available via the AmigaOS. So, the way blitz
does it is to store an area of the bitmap in a memory buffer and
then restore the area to the bitmap when you use unbuffer. So to
do this for a GFX card you'd have to write this kind of feature
yourself. If you know how to make your own 'BBlit.UnBuffer' function
with bitmaps (perhaps some kind of GetAShape system) you could
also do it with gfx cards (perhaps some kind of ReadPixelArray8
kind of system) I wouldn't lik to try it myself though.

> Or the ones from New Command Set? Is there generally a bb2
> command or do I have to use rtgmaster/cybergraphics.library?

It depends how your current gfx-card support is done. If you're using
a chunky buffer for your rendering the whole process would be
quite easy and I wouldn't be surprized if someone has already
implimented this kind of thing.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

