confronted head on by a blind tube mare."
-- Brass Eye




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_290" "Re: GFXCard Blitting"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@sdv.fr>
Date: Fri, 04 Dec 1998 17:17:40 +0100
Organization: Fantaisie Software
Subject: Re: GFXCard Blitting
Encoding: quoted-printable

    Hi Andreas, =


> Which command do I need to use for buffer blitting on a screen, that sh=
all
> also woek with gfx cards? Does BBlit and Unbuffer work with gfx cards?
> Or the ones from New Command Set? Is there generally a bb2 command or
> do I have to use rtgmaster/cybergraphics.library?

        NCS doesn't have build in buffer blit. It has a standard blitting=

routine (NCopyBitmap) but you should have a sort of GetAShape routine to
store the background before blitting. A note about NCS: all routines are =
for
now 100% OS friendly (ie, fully supported by GFX card). It's fully tested=
 on
a Picasso96 system, so I think it's enough..
 =

    Regards,

                        Fred.

