Just to add to the general confusion, I used to write Blitz programs on my trusty old A500+ with OS 2.05 (I think) and I
always used Gadget ID's below 50, with no problems at all.  I think I had my A1200 when all this 'use ID's higher than
50' thing started, so I have ever since, just in case my programs wouldn't work on someone else's machine.  So the
bottom line is:

I can neither confirm or deny that using or not using ID's above or below 50 on OS 2.xx will or will not give rise to
any problems.  I hope that clears things up (;

