 Yes.
 
> if so, that leads to question #2
> 
> 2. how would I go about it?

With a lot of hassle. Under OS3+ you can have custom rendering functions 
(implemented through the m,uch loved hook system) where you have to draw t=
he 
items in the listview yourself.

> if not
> 
> 3. would a gttext be possible to do it in?
> 

If you want to use a GTText, you may as well use your own text drawing rou=
tine 
and then put a GTBevelBox round it afterwards.

> and if not then...
>
> any idea on code to creats, say, a custom listview?? .. 
> 
> otherwise, maybe MUI!? ... but I would prefer to avoid MUI.. 

 Try to find a BOOPSI listview that does what you want, if you can. This i=
s as 
close to MUI as you can get without actually having to use it, and not hav=
ing 
to create your own interface.


