Hello Blitzers!

ok folks.. here it is.. I am now 100% positive, that text in a listview can be
output in different colors.. whether or not different in the same line or
not, remains to be seen, but I think that is also possible.. as of late, when
I run my pre-release of OrionIRC (now on Aminet), the listview bar tends to
be black and turn red when I click on it, and when I attempt to use a higher
gfx mode then 16 colors.. my listview display is filled with a different
color, for which reasons I have no idea, other then maybe a gfx card glitch,
which I doubt.. .. 

I have done a little bit of research, and reading.. and thanx to the recent
obtainment of he autodocs (many thanx all around!) I have some ideas to
bounce off your heads.. to see if it's feasable.. .. also: any information on
Boopsi, and using boopsi classes with blitz would be appreciated.. 

ok here it is.. I looked at the OS calls.. and was wondering if the following
calls would be able to effect it all.. .. as I was looking at the OS calls, I
was wondering if the problem didn't lay in Gadtools, but in graphics itself..
or even gadtools request to graphics.. .. in any case.. I surmised there had
to be a way to trick the system.. 

maybe there's a way, inside listview's own os routine to trick it.. I was
wondering in the middle listview update if a setrast() could be applied
somehow.. or even use a SetAPen() or SetBPen() may be applicable.. and if so,
how? .. 

Regards
-- 
           Andrew Drays (Condore) 

