The gadget to be activated is dependent upon user input.  I have (in
one example) five rows of two gadets per row.  The first for a
supplier name and the next for a monetary amount.  This is followed
by some more fields.
  
If the user hits return (or enter or Tab) on a blank supplier field
it means he's finished an so I skip to the other fields at the bottom
of the window.  If he enters a supplier name I activate the monetary
amount.  If he then enters a valid amount I activate the next
supplier, but if he enters an invalid amount I output an error message
and re-activate the amount field.  Easy for the user (and for me until
these ***** Tabs came along).
  
