@NODE "Mail_330" "GURU! - ILLEGAL Instruction"
 ([62.136.51.19] helo=sneech ident=paul)
	by mail7.svr.pol.co.uk with smtp (Exim 2.05iplimit-2 #5)
	id 0zlwkD-0004Od-00
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Fri, 4 Dec 1998 15:02:09 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Fri, 04 Dec 1998 14:49:40 +0000
Subject: GURU! - ILLEGAL Instruction

Hi,

I'm sure many have seen this error pop up once in a
while (GURU! - ILLEGAL Instruction) but does anyone
have any idea what causes it? The strange thing about
it is it usually points to an error somewhere else in the
code for example, today I did something very simple:

If OpenFile(4,"myfile")
  FileSeek 4,Lof(4)
  ...
  ...
EndIf

The GURU! error message came up at the FileSeek command
but this is inside a function that hasn't been touched for over
6 months and the routine has been working like this with no
problems. Of course, I'm using the debugger with full error
checking to in theory no normal problems occured before this
point.

I also got the same error earlier today but this time it was
durring a 'ReadMem' call. So, both times the error occured
durring file I/O so perhaps someone can give me a clue as
to what causes this error.

Cheers

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

"You berked-up little ape! (...) Sorry, I'm jamming on crusty white."
-- Brass Eye



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_331" "Re: GURU! - ILLEGAL Instruction"
          (Post.Office MTA v3.1.2 release (PO203-101c) ID# 0-0U10L2S100)
          with SMTP id AAA28968 for <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>;
          Sat, 5 Dec 1998 16:01:32 +0000
Date: Sat, 05 Dec 1998 15:50:45 +0000
From: Dave <d.boaz@virgin.net>
Subject: Re: GURU! - ILLEGAL Instruction
Encoding: 7bit

Paul Burkey wrote:
> 
> Hi,
> 
> I'm sure many have seen this error pop up once in a
> while (GURU! - ILLEGAL Instruction) but does anyone
> have any idea what causes it?

	I can`t remember exactly but I`ve had the error
	a few times,
	One time I think I fixed it by	putting `Even`
	after doing any INCBIN	type of instructions.
	
	Also I`ve noticed some commands have a strange effect on the
	debugger,
		such as `format`
		also you can`t use the longest form of the
		`window` command (the one where you fill in ALL parameters)
		inside a function seems to screw up a register it shouldn`t.

cyas

Dave/Blit




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_332" "Re: GURU! - ILLEGAL Instruction"
From: Mikkel =?iso-8859-1?Q?L=F8kke?= <FlameDuck@usa.net>
Date: Sat, 05 Dec 1998 18:09:21 +0200
Organization: A97
Subject: Re: GURU! - ILLEGAL Instruction
Encoding: quoted-printable
X-Info: mailto:sf@xxl.ots.dk in case of problems!

Hello Dave.

On 05-Dec-98, Dave wrote:
> Paul Burkey wrote:
>> =

>> Hi,
>> =

>> I'm sure many have seen this error pop up once in a
>> while (GURU! - ILLEGAL Instruction) but does anyone
>> have any idea what causes it?

>     I can`t remember exactly but I`ve had the error
>     a few times,
>     One time I think I fixed it by    putting `Even`
>     after doing any INCBIN    type of instructions.

Should only be a problem on 68000/68010 processors.

However, it might be because your machiine code isn't terminated by an RT=
S.
Or a subroutine/function/statement that isn't terminated properly, so the=

PC (Program Counter) runs amok in random memory.

Regards
-- =

