 ([62.136.35.149] helo=sneech ident=paul)
	by mail3.svr.pol.co.uk with smtp (Exim 2.05iplimit-2 #5)
	id 0zmUbY-0007Vv-00
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sun, 6 Dec 1998 03:11:28 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Sun, 06 Dec 1998 02:47:49 +0000
Subject: Re: GURU! - ILLEGAL Instruction

Hi,

>>> I'm sure many have seen this error pop up once in a
>>> while (GURU! - ILLEGAL Instruction) but does anyone
>>> have any idea what causes it?
>>
>>     One time I think I fixed it by    putting `Even`
>>     after doing any INCBIN    type of instructions.

> Should only be a problem on 68000/68010 processors.

yeah, that what I thought. Since I'm using an 040 I don't expect to see this
kind of even memory problem. My game will never support 68000/68010
either so this isn't something I'd like to worry about.

> Or a subroutine/function/statement that isn't terminated properly, so the
> PC (Program Counter) runs amok in random memory.

I think we've kind of worked out the problem here. It's probably when the
program counter runs amok OR the registers are getting corupted for
some reason. I've checked all the obvioud things but it looks like I'll
have to get into some serious bug finding here!

Cheers,

-- 
