Andreas Falkenhahn churned out *this* drivel :

> Sorry for this offtopic message but some checksum
> error on my HD really makes me go mad.
> 
> The checksum error is in one file in my root dir.
> How do I get rid of the corrupt file?? 

This sounds like a problem I've had twice in recent months.
I couldn't delete a file in any way at all, but while
fixing somthing else with DiskSalv, I got this file sorted
automatically. I think it was the Validate option (even if
the disk's bitmap is valid)...

When it was finished I was able to delete the file as normal...

> What programs do I need?

Go for DiskSalv - it's on Aminet...

See ya,
