Hi Mikkel L=F8kke :)

On 23-Dec-98, Mikkel L=F8kke wrote:

> Oh no.First it was PFS (Which was shareware), then it was AFS
(Which
> was a comercial package released by 4th Level Development) and now
> it's back to PFS, because too many people have trusted their HD's
> AFS and lost. :o) And isn't it strange that for a package that has
> been released for so long (8 years to my counting) there is still
not
> a single disc recovery program that fully supports it (Dave
Haynie's
> disksalv ALMOST does it.) The arguement is that PFS (AFS, whatever
> FS) is so good that it just isn't necesary. Strange then that the
> package carries a HUGE disclaimer, written all in capitols, in
bold,
> and in red writing that they won't take any responsibility for
> dataloss. I bought the original AFS package, and I have lost one HD
> (No, not just the files, an entire HD, completely fucked, in a
> hardware sense of way.) and another (different, obviously) HD that
> allthough it works today with FFS, still has wierd quirks
sometimes.
> I tell you, do not trust PFS more than you would Windoze98. (Which
is
> probably a bit harsh on the PFS/AFS guys, since it's not as crap as
> windows, but it gets an A for effort) :o)

That is an extreme misrepresentation of the facts.

AFS changed its name back to PFS2 for the simple reason that the
copyright reverted to the original creator from 4th Level
Developments. The name change  is because of the bad reputatino that
company built up due to its dubious business practices.

It is those same business practices that resulted in no disc recovery
programs supporting AFS.

The makers of PFS2 do not claim that no disk recovery program is
needed, that was 4th Level Development (who I've already explained
behaved didn't develop the software).

Indeed GREED even offer that if you send a knackered hard disk to them
they'll try to fix it for you.

In actual fact very few people have suffered serious data loss with
PFS/AFS.  Far less than have done so with FFS and disk recovery
programs.. There are thousands of very satisfied users out there.


Have fun
-- =

