A what ? My manual also doesn't metion this. Anyway whilst i was writing
some source for NetBlaster in DevPac 3, I compilede before AFS was done
saving, my machine crashed, and as I rebooted I noticed that my entire
"Programming" directory was mysteriously missing, and since there was no
Disc recovery software, what's a guy to do ? Atomic you say ? Like a Ther=
mo
Nuclear weapon ? (Another totally daff idea.)

> 2) PFS reorg in the background.  It dosn't matter if switch off
> whilsed it being down in the background, due to fact that PFS is a
> "atomic commit mechanis".

No PFS does not reorg in the background, it uses a completely different f=
ile
system sturucture  with relative block sizes, hence it does not have to
reorg.

> 3) Faster file access apporox over FFS 500%.

Yeah, on large files. But smaller files will not load at all until AFS's
buffer is filled, which means that certain programs actually won't work.
(UFO AGA is a good example) Now here comes the really wierd part, if you
have UFO on an FFS partition, on which it works, you can copy it to the A=
FS
partition, where it WON'T work, and then BACK to the FFS partition, and
guess what ? It suddenly won't work anymore !!! WOW !!! Also, my version =
of
AFS har a really hard time handling (Especially Deleteing) Really large
files, which is great if you're into CD-R software or Virtual Memeory.

> Flame Duck that end this war now please.

War ? I hardly think stating my opinion is war. Now if I was lame I would=

say things totally out of relevance, but I actually payed allmost =A380 f=
or a
program that fucked up my Harddisc. I think I'm entitled to thrash it
arround abit.


Regards
