@NODE "Mail_358" "Help Converting C to Blitz 2"
From: S Beardwood <scott@online.u-net.com>
Date: Wed, 23 Dec 1998 19:18:36 +0000
Organization: aMiGa wORlD oRDER
Subject: Help Converting C to Blitz 2
Encoding: 8bit

Hello,

Can any one help with converting the c source below to blitz.

UBYTE *Mod;
ULONG ModSize;

*struct TagItem ModAttrTags[]=
     {
      {DBMATTR_InstNum,0},
      {DBMATTR_ChanNum,0},
      {DBMATTR_PattNum,0},
      {DBMATTR_ModName,0},
      {DBMATTR_InstNames,0},
      {TAG_DONE,0}
     };


 ULONG InstrNum;
 ULONG ChanNum;
 ULONG PattNum;
 STRPTR ModName;
 STRPTR *InstNames;

ModAttrTags[0].ti_Data = (ULONG)&InstrNum;
ModAttrTags[1].ti_Data = (ULONG)&ChanNum;
ModAttrTags[2].ti_Data = (ULONG)&PattNum;
ModAttrTags[3].ti_Data = (ULONG)&ModName;
ModAttrTags[4].ti_Data = (ULONG)&InstNames;

printf("%d\n",InstrNum);
printf("%d\n",ChanNum);
printf("%d\n",PattNum);
printf("%s\n",ModName);

for(i=0;i<InstrNum;i++)
 {
  printf("%s\n",InstNames[i]);
  }


All The Best, 
