@NODE "Mail_359" "Re: Help Converting C to Blitz 2"
    24 Dec 98 11:53:38 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Thu, 24 Dec 1998 11:53:31 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Help Converting C to Blitz 2

If S Beardwood said to me "Help Converting C to Blitz 2", then I would say=
, OI! S,

> Can any one help with converting the c source below to blitz.

 Get a book about C, read it, do C.

; You need amigalibs.res resident, and this assumes that all the constants=
 are 
also in there.

DEFTYPE.b *_Mod;  Renamed, otherwise Mod may tokenise
DEFTYPE.l _ModSize; ditto

DEFTYPE.l _InstrNum ; More tokenising probs
DEFTYPE.l _ChanNum
DEFTYPE.l _PattNum
DEFTYPE.b *_ModName
DEFTYPE.l *_InstrNames

Dim _ModAttrTags.TagItem(6)
_ModAttrTags(0)\ti_Tag=3D#DBMATTR_InstNum,&_InstrNum
_ModAttrTags(1)\ti_Tag=3D#DBMATTR_ChanNum,&_ChanNum
_ModAttrTags(2)\ti_Tag=3D#DBMATTR_PattNum,&_PattNum
_ModAttrTags(3)\ti_Tag=3D#DBMATTR_ModName,&*_ModName
_ModAttrTags(4)\ti_Tag=3D#DBMATTR_InstNames,&*_InstrNames
_ModAttrTags(5)\ti_Tag=3D#TAG_END ; It should be end rather than done, to =
signify
                                ; end of tag array (same code, better for
                                ; reading)

NPrint _InstrNum
NPrint _ChanNum
NPrint _PattNum
NPrint Peek$(*_ModName)

For i.w=3D0 To _InstrNum-1
    *name.b =3D Peek.l(&*_InstrNames + Sizeof.l * i)
    NPrint Peek$(*name)
Next

 If it don't work, sorry won't ba back for two weeks.


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
  d.mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk ICQ=3D16827694
  http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn


