> 
> How do you do animation that is dependent on a fixed movement speed
> that appears to travel the same distance in a given space of time
> regardless of the framerate?

I (think) I see what you are asking.

How about linking your animation to a timer, for example do a Resettimer
when you do an animation frame, then when you go to do the next, check
Ticks to see how many Vblanks have gone by.  Now you can calculate your
movement based on this.

For example, if 1 tick you move 1 pixel, if 3 ticks move 3 pixels, etc.

Of course, it will get jerky if the framerate drops too low, but then, so
will everything else...
> 
> Also how do you calculate a table for use in remapping some graphics,
> ie finding the closest-matching colour in the palette to represent a
> decrease in brightness, for example?

Try reading the R-G-B values from the current setting of the colour in
question, then divide it by some amount (to decrease the brightness, say
each value *.8 for example) and look for the closeset match for this newly
calculated colour.
> 
> 
Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




