@NODE "Mail_377" "Re: How does Setint work?"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 09 Dec 1998 21:06:30 -0500
Subject: Re: How does Setint work?

Hi stocksjames

On 09-Dec-98, stocksjames wrote:
> Hi
>     I was wondering how 'setint' works. I usually include it to play
music:
> 
> Setint 5
>     PlayMed
> End Setint
> 
> Is 'PlayMed' executed on EVERY vertical refresh, or just those called by
> the program?

EVERY Vblank, no matter what your program is doing.  No matter if your main
loop takes 2 or more Vblanks to execute, or even if it is doing a WaitEvent
(ie, "sleeping" until something happens, the code in your SetInt will be
executed every 50th second (or 60th, or whatever depending on your
screenmode)_
_
BTW, your program can't really call a Vblank, it can only wait for one as
in:

Vwait.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




