On 09-Dec-98, amorel set out across the seas with this message:

->crappy. In the Blitz manual it STATES u have to use a setint 5 to

The Blitz manual lies =3D] You can pull a #PlayMed# out from absolutely
anywhere.  Except perhaps where the sun don't shine...  =3D$

<ahem>

Try assessing what the current scanrate is (don't ask me how) and then us=
ing
that value to execute the #PlayMed# every 50th of a frame.

eg something like :-

framerate.q=3D#EasyWayOfFindingTheScanRateWhichNoDoubtDoesNotExist_#
numberoftimestoexecuteplaymed.q=3Dframerate/50
counter.q=3D0
#While# #Joyb#(0)=3D0
  counter+1
  #If# counter>numberoftimestoexecuteplaymed
    counter-numberoftimestoexecuteplaymed
    #PlayMed#
  #EndIf#
#Wend#

You get the idea =3D]

-- =


