@NODE "Mail_384" "Re: How does Setint work?"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 11 Dec 1998 05:17:00 -0500
Subject: Re: How does Setint work?

Hi,

On 10-Dec-98, Anton Reinauer wrote:
> On 11-Dec-98, amorel wrote:
> 
>> so how do other players play a med then? Or is it that just the blitz
>> playmed routine needs scanrate timing? 
> 
>  They use CIA interupts instead- which are independant of scanrate.

BTW, the Blitz playmed DOES NOT need scanrate timing.  It simply needs SOME
SORT of timing, as you must call it yourself.  Although it is easiest to do
this with a Vblank Interrupt (scranrate) you could call it with your own
CIA timer routine.

There is an example in the MaVaTi examples in dev/basic that shows using
the
CIA timer.

But probably better would be to try to find the .fd files and autodoc for
the medplayer.library and fd-convert it so you can access the
medplayer.library directly for yourself.

Later...
-- 
