@NODE "Mail_392" "Re: how to do a commodity with blitz?"
 ([62.136.47.160] helo=194.152.64.35 ident=loki)
	by mail4.svr.pol.co.uk with smtp (Exim 2.05iplimit-2 #5)
	id 0zolTA-0000nj-00
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sat, 12 Dec 1998 09:36:12 +0000
From: Loki <loki@napalmdeath.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Sat, 12 Dec 1998 09:30:51 +0000
Organization: Silicon Systems [s^S]^98`99
Subject: Re: how to do a commodity with blitz?

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.272041352.3
Encoding: binary

Hello Christian

OI! Christian!... on 11-Dec-98 you wrote to me about how to do a commodity
with blitz? and stuff... so i thought i`d reply! :)
CU>> Hello blitzers!
CU>> 
CU>> Can any one help me and explain me with an example how can i do a
system
CU>> comodity with blitz???
CU>> 
CU>> So if there's no exaple can any one tell me where to start???

Tis quite simple really,... Here you go,.

*START CODE*


; EXAMPLE CODE -
; 1998, SATANIC DREAMS SOFTWARE.

WBStartup:WBenchToFront_:FindScreen 0

wINwID=220
wINhI=57
Active=1
Interface=1

Gosub OpenGUI


; Open the program as a commodity, (This is what will appear in Exchange)
If MakeCommodity("Example Program","Example Commodity","This is an example
of a Commodity")=0
  tmp=Request("Request","Could not open commodity,|Due to lack of
memory!","Ok!")
  Goto EndMe
EndIf

Repeat
  VWait
  Ev.l=Event
  Em.l=ExchangeMessage
  Ce.l=CommodityEvent ;Must be used!

  Select Em
    Case $00000013   ;Show Interface HIT!
      If Interface=0
        Gosub OpenGUI
        Interface=1
      EndIf
    Case $00000015   ;Hide Interface HIT!
      If Interface=1
        Gosub CloseGUI
        Interface=0
      EndIf
    Case $0000000F   ;InActive HIT!
      WindowOutput 0
      Active=0
      Gosub PrintActive
    Case $00000011   ;Active HIT!
      WindowOutput 0
      Active=1
      Gosub PrintActive
  End Select

Until Ev=$200 OR Em=$00000017 ; $17 is REMOVE so it closes your program.


EndMe
  Gosub CloseGUI
  End



OpenGUI
  SizeLimits wINwID,wINhI,wINwID,wINhI
  Window
0,ScreenWidth/2-(wINwID/2),ScreenHeight/2-(wINhI/2),wINwID,wINhI,$1000|$400|$2|$4|$8|$1|$20,"",1,$80
  WTitle "Example Program","Example Program.."
  WindowOutput 0
    WLocate 5,4
    Print "Open Exchange and try some stuff."
  Gosub PrintActive
Return


CloseGUI
  CloseWindow 0
Return

PrintActive
  Select Active
    Case 0
      Act$="NO"
    Case 1
      Act$="YES"
  End Select
  WLocate 5,20
  Print "Active = ",Act$,"  "
Return

; END CODE!

*END CODE*

Attached is the same code,..

Hope this helps,. Cyaz,.

-- 
<tsb>
<tsb>Contacting Me:
<tsb>E-MAIL: loki@napalmdeath.freeserve.co.uk
<tsb>

--BOUNDARY.272041352.3
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="CommodityExample.asc"
Encoding: binary
Content-Description: Commodities in Blitz Example,.


; EXAMPLE CODE -
; 1998, SATANIC DREAMS SOFTWARE.

WBStartup:WBenchToFront_:FindScreen 0

wINwID=220
wINhI=57
Active=1
Interface=1

Gosub OpenGUI


; Open the program as a commodity, (This is what will appear in Exchange) <G>
If MakeCommodity("Example Program","Example Commodity","This is an example of a Commodity")=0
  tmp=Request("Request","Could not open commodity,|Due to lack of memory!","Ok!")
  Goto EndMe
EndIf

Repeat
  VWait
  Ev.l=Event
  Em.l=ExchangeMessage
  Ce.l=CommodityEvent ;Must be used!

  Select Em
    Case $00000013   ;Show Interface HIT!
      If Interface=0
        Gosub OpenGUI
        Interface=1
      EndIf
    Case $00000015   ;Hide Interface HIT!
      If Interface=1
        Gosub CloseGUI
        Interface=0
      EndIf
    Case $0000000F   ;InActive HIT!
      WindowOutput 0
      Active=0
      Gosub PrintActive
    Case $00000011   ;Active HIT!
      WindowOutput 0
      Active=1
      Gosub PrintActive
  End Select

Until Ev=$200 OR Em=$00000017 ; $17 is REMOVE so it closes your program.


EndMe
  Gosub CloseGUI
  End



OpenGUI
  SizeLimits wINwID,wINhI,wINwID,wINhI
  Window 0,ScreenWidth/2-(wINwID/2),ScreenHeight/2-(wINhI/2),wINwID,wINhI,$1000|$400|$2|$4|$8|$1|$20,"",1,$80
  WTitle "Example Program","Example Program.."
  WindowOutput 0
    WLocate 5,4
    Print "Open Exchange and try some stuff."
  Gosub PrintActive
Return


CloseGUI
  CloseWindow 0
Return

PrintActive
  Select Active
    Case 0
      Act$="NO"
    Case 1
      Act$="YES"
  End Select
  WLocate 5,20
  Print "Active = ",Act$,"  "
Return

; END CODE!


--BOUNDARY.272041352.3--




