@NODE "Mail_400" "Re: IsCyberModeID (Can P96 users test it?)"
 ([195.92.235.226] helo=allhours.karoo.co.uk ident=Jeepster)
	by svr-a-05.core.theplanet.net with smtp (Exim 2.02 #2)
	id 0zlgXg-000807-00
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Thu, 3 Dec 1998 21:44:08 +0000
From: Thomas Newsom <thomas.newsom@allhours.karoo.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 03 Dec 1998 21:39:48 +0100
Organization: The Open All Hours BBS @ +44-(0)1482-345494 & +44-(0)1482-447576 24 hours
Subject: Re: IsCyberModeID (Can P96 users test it?)

Hello Paul,

> Anyway, I've attached an archive that contains a test program
> that will open a requester and attempt to detect foreign modes
> using a mixture of IsCyberModeID and the DisplayInfo structure.
> Coul someone with P96 test this out for me? I'm hoping it will
> work with P96 as well as CyberGFX.

> I've included the simple source code and also the ready converted
> 'cybergraphics.library1' blitz lib that is required for this special
> function. The source is a bit crude but it should do it's job! :)

ModeName: PicassoII:1120x832  8bit
CyberGraphX API available (cound be Picasso96)
ModeType: Foreign (IsCyberModeID)

Is the return info I got using P96 with a Picasso II+ GFX card.

Cheers,
-- 
Tom.

