From: Paul Burkey <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Fri, 04 Dec 1998 02:15:02 +0000
Subject: Re: IsCyberModeID (Can P96 users test it?)

Hi,

> ->I've included the simple source code and also the ready converted
> ->'cybergraphics.library1' blitz lib that is required for this special
> ->function. The source is a bit crude but it should do it's job! :)

> One question.  If you don't have cybergraphics.library in LIBS: will Blitz
> crash?  ;]

Of course not. The OpenLibrary function is used to check if it exists
or not. If cybergraphics.library isn't available it won't use it. Check
the source code to see how that works.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

