@NODE "Mail_409" "Re:FIX for SuperTed Help Menu!!"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 27 Dec 1998 08:37:18 -0500
Subject: Re:FIX for SuperTed Help Menu!!

Hi Jean-Marc

On 26-Dec-98, Jean-Marc GIGANDET wrote:
> Hello Curt
> 
> If you edit the menu ("Custom", item "Edit"), and select Help, you should
> find this Cmd :
>      Run >NIL: Blitz2:RedHelp/RED_HELP LIB="%g" CMD="%t" PORT="%r"
> SCREEN="%s"
> 
> Of course, you need Rexx running (as for TedDock), and RED_HELP program
in
> the "Blitz2:RedHelp" directory, and help (for acid libraries and RED
ones),
> in their drawers ("Blitz2:RedHelp/AcidGuides",
> "Blitz2:RedHelp/REDBlitzLibs"). That should work.

No, everything was set as you said, but still it didn't work.

I have found the problem, and maybe other people have it too, so I am
passing it along:

In the RedHelp/ drawer is the file "RED_HELP".  It did NOT have it's
"Script" bit set.  Once I fixed this, everything works properly!  YAY!! 
Very useful!

To fix, just select the "RED_HELP" icon, and "Information" on the WB menu. 
Now set the "Script" bit and save it.

Later...
-- 
I haven't lost my mind; it's backed up on tape somewhere.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




