@NODE "Mail_411" "Re: Lib probs"
    22 Dec 98 17:12:09 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 22 Dec 1998 17:12:05 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Lib probs

Hi Bippy,

 Ahhh, I see now. You've got either an old version of Blitz or an old vers=
ion 
of one of the lib manager programs. Do you have an acidlibs and a deflibs?=
 If 
yes, then the lib manager is most definately lying to you, as the only thi=
ngs 
in acidlibs is the libraries written by acid - all others (including 
fdconverted ones) are in deflibs (or not, Mikkel :). You don't need to bot=
her 
with any of the lib managers, you can get along fine with thses three prog=
rams:
    NewFDConvert
    makedeflibs
    viewlibs

 The source to the last two were on a BUM, I'll send them to you if you do=
n't 
have them. Basically what to do is this:
    Create the viewlibs and makedeflibs executables, and put them in C:
    Get a list of libnums by doing 'viewlibs > ram:libnums.txt' (in CLI)
    Find a suitable lib number by looking at the libnums.txt file (around =
200 
for fdconverted libs)
    Run NewFDConvert - select the .fd and appropriate library
    create new deflibs by running 'makedeflibs' (in CLI)

 The fd you sent me was knackered, so I downloaded the full archive, and d=
one 
the above. I ended up with a mpega.library1 in Blitzlibs:userlibs, and I u=
sed 
lib num 212 (although you don't have to use the same number). Commands tok=
enise 
fine.


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
  d.mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk ICQ=3D16827694
  http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn


@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_412" "Re: Lib probs"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 24 Dec 1998 07:07:22 -0500
Subject: Re: Lib probs

Hi everyone,

On 22-Dec-98, David Mcminn wrote:
> Hi Bippy,
> 
> Ahhh, I see now. You've got either an old version of Blitz or an old
> version of one of the lib manager programs. Do you have an acidlibs and a
> deflibs? If yes, then the lib manager is most definately lying to you, as
> the only things in acidlibs is the libraries written by acid - all others
> (including fdconverted ones) are in deflibs (or not, Mikkel :). You don't
> need to bother with any of the lib managers, you can get along fine with
> thses three programs:
>    NewFDConvert
>    makedeflibs
>    viewlibs

Being the lazy guy I am, I made a few improvements to James' excellent
NewFDconvert, so now it will scan your BlitzLibs: directories and present
you a list of all open library numbers, with the highest available library
number pre-selected as the default.

It will also refuse to make a library with a clashing library number to one
that already exists.  We are testing it now to be sure it all works OK -
watch for it soon.

If anyone wants to help in the testing, write me direct for a beta copy of
the source.

Then you will no longer need to mess with the viewlibs bit...

You will still need to makedeflibs, if you use one.

-- 
A day without sunshine is like, you know, night.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




