From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 28 Dec 1998 18:02:57 -0500
Subject: Re: libs

Hi Paul,

On 28-Dec-98, Paul wrote:
> hi.
> 
> I've been trying to remake the fd file for graphics.library so that it
> tokenises the v40 WriteChunkyPixels_().
> 
> So far it does tokenise it, but now it's bloody saying that lib number
> 19 doesn't exist ($13).
> 
> I put the two new graphics libs to lib numbers 254 and 250 as that was
> the numbers of the libs originally. But any idea what lib 19 might be
> as I don't seem to have it and yet it's never complained before. Ted
> doesn't jump to any line when it reports the error, and it reports it
> the instant you try to compile.
> 
> Any suggestions appreciated, before I throw it out the window.

If this helps, I have no library #19 either, and my graphics.library1 is 254
and graphics.library2 is 250, same as yours.  These are the originals, not
new ones.

Did you possibly reverse them?  This might cause a problem with an already
tokenized source (ie, not saved as ascii)

A possible suggestion (which seems weird but often fixes this sort of stuff
for me) is to try deleting the first line of your code (or wherever the
cursor is when you try to compile it) and re-type it.  It seems that
sometimes odd unseen characters occasionally wind up in my code, which
Blitz tries to read as tokens...

