 Drag's quite fun once you get into it....(ahem)

 You can insert items anywhere in a Blitz type list. But you could try Dim=
'ming 
the list to a huge number (probably 2^15-1 is the largest Blitz will allow=
).

 Alternatively use the exec OS calls (Insert, AddHead, RemHead, etc.) for 
manipulating lists. They're easy enough to use. I had started writing a bu=
nch 
of functions which did exactly the same as the Blitz list stuff, but retur=
ned 
the pointers instead of -1, allowing themm to be manipulated by hand as we=
ll. I 
haven't bothered finishing it though. The only problem with doing this is =
that 
you can't easily use Blitz created GTListviews (as they expect Blitz type 
lists). You could of course switch to the NCS or OS in that case.


