> If any of you can provide any of the following, please REPLY to this
mail.
> 
> The game will include:
> 
> 256 Colour Gamplay
> 32 Colour Backgrounds (with COPPER for background Gradient).

Why are you using the COPPER? This surely means you'll be programming in
SLOW/PLANAR Blitz mode?

Why HALF you potential market by creating something which will require a med
spec machine (for which most people have a cheap SVGA monitor) and can only
be used by people with TV's and Multiscan monitors?

What with all the Chunky stuff being talke about and Paul Wests Mildred C2P
system, why not make the game Amiga friendly?

Just a thought!

