@NODE "Mail_422" "Lotus 3 Clone"
From: Jamie Bentley <sniper@technet2000.com.au>
Date: Mon, 07 Dec 1998 13:19:57 +0500
Organization: Sniper Productions
Subject: Lotus 3 Clone
Encoding: quoted-printable

 Blitzers,

 As mentioned earlier (6 hours earlier, but both mails have been sent at =
same
time), we have come out with some basic plans for the Lotus 3 game.

 If any of you can provide any of the following, please REPLY to this mai=
l.

 The game will include:

 256 Colour Gamplay
 32 Colour Backgrounds (with COPPER for background Gradient).
 All gfx will be pre-raytraced and landscapes will contains 40 Frames eac=
h
(starting from small to very large) to simulate movement.
 There will be 4 different car colours and 4 different types of car.
 The only realtime "rendering" in the game will be of the road itself, th=
is
may not be the case as we have yet to consult any programmers on any
alternative rendering methods (the Road MUST have texture).
 As of yet it is still unknown if the roadside (everything that isn't the=

road) will be COPPER or textured, or BOTH.

 We ran over the feasibility of such a game and realised that it is nothi=
ng
that nobody has done before, and so the game will contain cut scenes, cra=
sh
scenes, and other various gameplay features which are not to be discussed=

until completion (unless with the programmer him/herself).

 If you are interested in programming such a game, we have openings for t=
he
following areas of programming.

 1) Actual Game engine (background movement, road movement, cars etc).
 2) TCP/IP network programming  (for up to 4 players, or  2 on linkup).
 3) Frontend (Title, options etc), introduction animation.

 Please Email me direct, and not through blitz list. Publisher has alread=
y
been notified and has agreed to comply provided demo version of game is u=
p to
scratch.

 Thank you for your time (I hope I haven't bored you).

 Jamie Bentley - Sniper Productions=A9 (Since 1995)
