Hi Jarv,

> 	I don't really see why a copper background is necessary. You'll get
> a much nicer back drop if you use graphics. People only used gradient skies
> in the past becuae it used less mem than a backdrop. These days, memory is
> the least of your worries.

I don't recall doing copper backgrounds as a result of not having
graphical backgrounds. Even if I had graphics background I would also
have a copper rainbow. Mainly the reason I used them was because they
were quite efficient and added a lot more apparent colour to the
display, not to mention using it to split the display into different
palettes to surpass the maximum technically allowed.

