@NODE "Mail_434" "MiniMildred"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Tue, 8 Dec 1998 17:45:17 +0000
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 8 Dec 98 17:44:02 +0000
Subject: MiniMildred
Encoding: 7bit

Hi.

As i already have Milred installed, I found that when installing
MiniMildred also I had a strange thing happen with the tokens.

Typing MMc2pCPUmode, for example, tokenised as MSMaskScrollShape. The
library numbers don't clash.

Anyone know why this might be?

It isn't a deadly effect, as generally you wont want both libraries in
use at the same time, but its a pain.

-- 
Paul.

IRC: #amiga, Dalnet: #blitz
WWW: http://www.stationone.demon.co.uk
E-M: paul@stationone.demon.co.uk



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_435" "More Blitz Source Check"
 ([62.136.37.84] helo=sneech ident=paul)
	by mail2.svr.pol.co.uk with smtp (Exim 2.05iplimit-2 #5)
	id 0zm1TC-0003iH-00
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Fri, 4 Dec 1998 20:04:54 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Fri, 04 Dec 1998 19:59:03 +0000
Subject: More Blitz Source Check

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1743337480.1

Hi,

I just added an extra feature to the BlitzSourceCheck program so
it now detects unnecessarily SHARED variables. It's certainly not
foolproof so it will miss about 20% of them but it does catch most.
I tested it on Foundation which has over 260 functions and it
found 95 unnecessarily shared variables. Am I right in presuming
that shared variables take a small about of time? Any idea what
exactly happens to shared vars? Anyway, whether it's a good
optimizing feature or simply a nice 'tidy up' feature, here it is.

Remember, I do know it's not perfect and it's certainly going to
miss a few errors but this util is only a few hours old, be patient! :)

I doubt I'll be doing any more for a few days so please pardon the
fact that I posted an older version only an hour ago! :)

Cheers

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

--BOUNDARY.1743337480.1
