    Hi Paul, =


> I just added an extra feature to the BlitzSourceCheck program so
> it now detects unnecessarily SHARED variables. It's certainly not
> foolproof so it will miss about 20% of them but it does catch most.
> I tested it on Foundation which has over 260 functions and it
> found 95 unnecessarily shared variables. Am I right in presuming
> that shared variables take a small about of time? Any idea what
> exactly happens to shared vars? Anyway, whether it's a good
> optimizing feature or simply a nice 'tidy up' feature, here it is.

    Sorry to say that, but removing unused SHARED variable doens't change=

anything... It's a COMPILER  command which say if BB2 should create other=

variables or use the already defined variable. =


