@NODE "Mail_442" "Re: More screen and system related issues..."
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Wed, 30 Dec 1998 13:57:31 +0000
From: "David McMinn" <dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk>
Organization: International House of Mojo
Date: Wed, 30 Dec 1998 13:49:25 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: More screen and system related issues...

On 30 Dec 98, at 4:55, Mikkel broke out long enough to write:

You'll need amigalibsii.res for all these solutions.

> A. How to find out what colour the title bar is.

On OS3+ (its not supported under lower versions) one of the pens in the dr=
aw 
info structure of the screen tells you what pen the screen bar is rendered=
 in.

*scr._Screen =3D Peek.l(Addr Screen(#screennum); Assuming you don't alread=
y have 
                                             ; a pointer to your screen
*di.DrawInfo =3D GetScreenDrawInfo_(*scr)
If *di
  If *di\dri_Version >=3D 2    ; Check for OS3+
    barpen.w =3D Peek.w(*di\dri_Pens + Sizeof.w * #BARBLOCKPEN)
    ; In here, you can use Blitz commands like Red(barpen) etc if you
    ; need the actual component values, or you can use an OS call like
    ; allcols.w =3D GetRGB4(*scr\ViewPort\ColorMap, barpen)
    ; and then split up the colours - 4 bits per colour green=3D0-3, blue
    ; =3D4-7, red=3D8-11
    ; I can't remember but that ViewPort above may be _ViewPort
  End If
End If

> B. How to find out whether a font is fixed width or proportionel.

There's a flag in the Flags field of the textfont structure. Assuming you =
don't 
already have a pointer to your textfont structure:

*tf.TextFont =3D Peek.l(Addr IntuiFont(#fontnum) + 8)
If *tf\tf_Flags & #FBF_PROPORTIONAL
  NPrint "Proportional font"
Else
  NPrint "Fixed width font"
End If

> C. And (I know it has been asked before) that thing with the TextLegth
> system thingy ? Thank you for your patiance :o)

Grrr.

OK, If you have a window open, do this:

WindowFont #fontnum
a$=3D"Blah blah blah"
tlen.w =3D TextLength_(RastPort(#windownum), &a$, Len(a$))
; tlen contains the length in pixels of "Blah blah blah" for
; any font

or if you don't have any window:
DEFTYPE._RastPort rp
InitRastPort_ &rp
SetFont_ &rp, Peek.l(Addr Intuifont(#fontnum) + 8)
a$=3D"Blah blah blah"
tlen.w =3D TextLength_(RastPort(#windownum), &a$, Len(a$))
; tlen contains the length in pixels of "Blah blah blah" for
; any font


[) /\ \/ ][ [)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
 dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk
  http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn


@ENDNODE
