From: "Oliver Marks" <oly@enterprise.net>
Organization: Private
Date: 19 Dec 98 21:49:45 +0000
Subject: Re: Moreentries not working :-(
Encoding: 7bit

Hi,
> 
> > I have been having problems with some code i wrote a while ago i
> > remember that it definatly worked the problem is the moreentries
> > command it always returns a value of 0 even if there are directorys in
> > the path i set.
> > I have also tryed the example code this has the same error that the
> > moreentries command allways returns a value of 0.
> > Does anyone have any idea what could be causing this. 
> 
> Well, to be honest I don't even know what the MoreEntries command does, it
> certainly tokenizes okay in my editor. Which library is it from, and what
> does it do ? (Not that I've had much use for it, obviously) :o)

It is part of the elmore dos library it is used to test to see if
there are any files in a directory and can be used with other commands
like entryname$ to read in all the files in a directory.


@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_448" "Re: Moreentries not working :-("
From: Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
Date: Sun, 20 Dec 1998 13:55:53 +1300
Subject: Re: Moreentries not working :-(

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.2016239232.1

On 19-Dec-98, Oliver Marks wrote:
> Hi,
> 
> I have been having problems with some code i wrote a while ago i
> remember that it definatly worked the problem is the moreentries
> command it always returns a value of 0 even if there are directorys in
> the path i set.
> I have also tryed the example code this has the same error that the
> moreentries command allways returns a value of 0.
> Does anyone have any idea what could be causing this. 

     Yeah, the lib was changed around Blitz 1.8, and not documented! 
Here's a code snippet that should help :)
-- 
        Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
      
--BOUNDARY.2016239232.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="More entries.asc"
Encoding: quoted-printable


    Examine( Planets$)
    While MoreEntries
        File_Name$=3DEntryName$
        If NOT EntryDir
            If Right$(File_Name$,5) <> ".info"
                ResetList planets()
                While NextItem (planets())
                    If Left$(planets(),Len(planets()))=3DLeft$(File_Name$=
,Len(File_Name$)-4)
                        Goto Escape
                    EndIf
                Wend


--BOUNDARY.2016239232.1--




@ENDNODE
