@NODE "Mail_468" "Re: OS Question"
From: "BootBlock/Carnage" <BootBlock@Bigfoot.com>
Subject: Re: OS Question
Date: Fri, 1 Jan 1999 00:29:16 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit


Rui wrote:

>Hello,

>Does anyone now how to use the Setcomment_(name,comment) function...
>It hangs my computer when i try to use it...

You have to supply both parameters with the *address* of the strings, like
so:

Filename$ = "RAM:MyFile"
Comment$ = "Whooo! A comment type jobby!"

If SetComment_(&Filename$,&Comment$)=0
  DisplayBeep_ 0
  NPrint "Error setting comment!"
  VWait 50
Endif


--
