@NODE "Mail_469" "Re:Lotus3 thing"
From: "C.J.R.Jarvis" <C.J.R.Jarvis@wkac.ac.uk>
Subject: Re:Lotus3 thing
Date: Wed, 9 Dec 1998 14:09:33 -0000 
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Hello there,
	I don't really see why a copper background is necessary. You'll get
a much nicer back drop if you use graphics. People only used gradient skies
in the past becuae it used less mem than a backdrop. These days, memory is
the least of your worries.
	Furthermore, on the basis of you worrying that the game will be all
that's done before, it would be better to add elements to the gameplay,
rather than relying on gimmicks.
	Games like lotus are limited because the driving is all there is in
the game.
	Include championships, 16-player tournaments, races for money to
upgrade the car. Stuff to add variety without it becoming bogged down in a
sim.
	Also, if using OS-friendly screens, you can have a four-player mode,
using, say, a separate 160x128 bitmap for each players, and then
BitmapToWindowing each of the bitmaps to four windows. That would be cool.
	Chris Jarvis


