@NODE "Mail_480" "Re: pick up words from screen"
From: Sami =?iso-8859-1?Q?N=E4=E4t=E4nen?= <sami.naatanen@dlc.fi>
Date: Sat, 19 Dec 1998 01:20:05 +0300
Subject: Re: pick up words from screen
Encoding: quoted-printable

On 18-Dec-98, Mikkel L=F8kke wrote.

>   Hello Sven.
>   =

>   On 17-Dec-98, Sven Dr=F6ge wrote:
>  >>> ->> If need a functions that returns a string containing the word
>  >>> ->> mousepointer.
>  >>> ->> Each word (in a window, on the screen, titlebar). Is that poss=
ible
>   ?
>  >> =

>  >>> ->No.
>  >> =

>  >>> Well, yes, it is, but there's only a hard way : You'll need to rem=
ember
>  >> the
>  >>> co-ords of each piece of text and check when the mousepointer is o=
n top
>  >> of
>  >>> it...
>  >> =

>  >> Ah, you assume he wrote the text himself. I assumed he was trying t=
o
>   make
>  > a
>  >> PowerSnap type utility. :o)
>  > That is exactly what I want to do:
>   =

>   Yeah, I figured as much :o)
>   =

>  > How is the little tool ConClip (startup-sequence) realized ???
>   =

>   Well, I think it has something to do with using the console.device, b=
ut I
>   really havn't a clue. (Me think it magic) :o)
>   =


Well PowerSnap gets the window font and then searches character matching
from the windows bitmap. If any found then it will start geting character=
s
from that point. In some cases it just can't do the job. (multiple fonts
used in window or background isn't solid.) MCP have a powersnap version
which can snap from multi coloured background and can handle multiple
fonts. It will ofcourse slow it down the more fonts you add to the snap
list.

