It's s3m, ScreamTracker Modules, and no-one uses them anymore either. :o)=

Then there is xm, which is FastTracker, which some people use. The bigges=
t
problem in making software to play these PC type modules is that they oft=
en
use 16 bit samples iin more than 4 channels, requireing mixing and stuff.=

Thank god for AHI, allthough people prefer to write their own routines to=

reduce CPU overhead, in BLITZ (Unless you're a seasoned ASM coder) AHI is=

probably the best way to go.

> And whats more rewarding than using your own player? =3D)

Useing someone else's. That works :o)


Regards
