    23 Dec 98 08:54:44 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Wed, 23 Dec 1998 08:54:36 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Q

On 22 Dec 98, at 19:38, Paul wrote:

> Does anyone know how to get the o/s 3.1 function `WriteChunkyPixels_' to
> become a token in Blitz?

Curt's right, get the .fd (Devs CD) for the OS3.1 graphics.library (I thin=
k 
thats where it is??) and fdconvert it. I recently fdconverted all the os3.=
1 
stuff, and its all fine, but as I don't have the 3.1 WB disks, I can't 
fdconvert some of them.
 
> Does anyone know where in memory/structs to obtain a number
> representing what CPU the user has (as returned by the Processor
> instrurction)?

 Tsk, tsk, don't randomly jab about in memory. Its possible to read the 
AttnFlags in the execbase, (*e.ExecBase =3D Peek.l(4):*e\AttnFlags) but th=
ats a 
big future compatible no-no (I don't even know if that has flags for PPCs,=
 it 
doesn't normally for 060). Check out the includes for the processor flags.=
 Also 
the Devs CD tells you how to read what processor you have properly, but I =
can't 
remember if it was an OS function, or reading the AttnFlags but having to 
change your program when a new version of the OS came out.

> Does anyone know how to find out what version of o/s is available
> (with regards the WriteChunkyPixels thing)?

 You could read the version field in the libnode field in the execbase:), =
but 
again thats probably a future compatibility no-no:
      *e.ExecBase =3D Peek.l(4)
      NPrint "OS Version: ", *e\LibNode\lib_Version

