I would also do this via ExecBase and the processor flags...But the
best way (also PPC then) would be to use identify.library which
got alot of system identification methods
> 
> Does anyone know how to find out what version of o/s is available
> (with regards the WriteChunkyPixels thing)?
You may use the dos.library call getvar() to retreive Kickarts version:

*buf.b=AllocVec_(8,$10001)
ver$="Kickstart" ; or Workbench etc.
GetVar_ &ver$,*buf,7,0
Nprint Peek$(*buf)  ; -> version is stored in *buf
FreeVec_ *buf

That should also work with future versions of the OS (if there
ever will be any ;-)
