Well I don't know if I correctly understood everything talked above, but
if the question where about using address $4 to find where exec library i=
s?
Then this is totaly leagal AND THE ONLY WAY! Just by thinking logically:

To open a library you need to use OpenLibrary. And to use OpenLibrary
you will need to know the baseaddress of the library where OpenLibrary
lies. Because OpenLibrary is function from Exec library you need to know
the execbase to be able to open library! So what's the point to open the
exec library if you already know the same info as you did before?

If you where meaning the modification of the execbase or the exec library=
=2E
then you really are in the area of no-no!

The only guys who are the permission to write to these kind of addresses
are the OS programmers!


