@NODE "Mail_517" "Quake Clone cancelled"
From: Jamie Bentley <sniper@technet2000.com.au>
Date: Mon, 07 Dec 1998 13:08:35 +0500
Organization: Sniper Productions
Subject: Quake Clone cancelled
Encoding: quoted-printable

 Heya all,

 We decided that a polygon Quake  clone was completely out of the questio=
n due
to lack of interest (out of 50 people, only 21 said they were interested)=
=2E

 And to add to this, a decent version of the game would require at least =
An
030/882 with Pixel64 card (135mhz).

 These are not widely used at this point in time.

 Brett Round, the group's head programing anaylyst (he works out the
feasibility of such things) said that even on an 030/882, simple polygon
routines were fine, but for highly levels of details (IE: Polygon texture=
s
etc) would be pushed down to 10fps at 320x200!

 This was obviously far too slow to bother with.

 While the project was cancelled, ideas and thoughts are still going into=
 it
in case anybody else would like to head the project (please Email me).

 Our next plan is a clone of "Lotus 3", but with more power and possibili=
ty of
net games.

 I will be asking if anybody is up to it (programming), at a later date.

 Designs for the game are sketchy at current but more info will be added
later.

 For any inquiries please reply to this mail.

Jamie Bentley - Sniper Productions=A9 1995
