@NODE "Mail_519" "Re: Quest"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 24 Dec 1998 07:35:16 -0500
Subject: Re: Quest

Hi amorel

On 23-Dec-98, amorel wrote:
> I`ve still not figured out why many os function dont work anymore here.
If
> for example I try to use request I type in <request_> and it shows up in
> blue. But when I try to compile it the compiler says syntax error. I
can`t
> figure out why, as it DID show up in blue. I bet I overlook sth really
> obvious :-\

This means you are giving it wrong parameters, or not enough.
The command will tokenize (turn blue) because Blitz found it, but you must
still use it correctly.

Example:

correct:
Request "A requester","OK","It works"

wrong:
Request "A requester","OK"      ;SYNTAX ERROR!  (it needs 3 parameters)

wrong:
Request "A requester",167,"OK"  ;ERROR!  it must be 3 strings, with quotes.


If you are using it as a Function (returns a value) you must call it like
this:

correct:
answer.b=Request ("A Requester","Do you want to quit?","Yes|No")

if you forgot the "(" or ")" you will get SYNTAX ERROR

also wrong:

Request ("A Requester","Do you want to quit?","Yes|No")  SYNTAX ERROR -
there is no place for the function to return the value!
> And where can I find some xample source to do
> trivial things like unpacking ppp

There is an example of unpacking PowerPacker files by James Boyd in
Aminet/dev/basic  and also on my web page.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




