 via smail with P:esmtp/R:smart_host/T:smtp
	(sender: <Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de>) 
	id <m0ztCyW-001nxiC@insider.regio.net>
	for <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>; Thu, 24 Dec 1998 16:46:56 +0100 (MET)
	(Smail-3.2.0.101 1997-Dec-17 #1 built DST-Jul-17)
From: Andreas Falkenhahn <Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de>
Date: Thu, 24 Dec 1998 16:39:15 +0100
Organization: Airsoft Softwair
Subject: Re: Quest

Hi amorel
Am 23-Dez-98 schrieb amorel:

> I`ve still not figured out why many os function dont work anymore here.
If
> for example I try to use request I type in <request_> and it shows up in
> blue. But when I try to compile it the compiler says syntax error. I
can`t
> figure out why, as it DID show up in blue. I bet I overlook sth really
> obvious :-\
Using the os call Request() is a bit complicated so you might
better use the blitz function Request() (simply remove the "_").
That`s alot easier. But if you want me to explain os call Request()
 then i`ll do so....but in this case it`s normally not necessary (only
if you want to os call optimize your program like hell :))
> 
> And in my ongoing search for a (octa)med playing routines, could anyone
> help me out with this? And where can I find some xample source to do
> trivial things like unpacking ppp, xpk files and stuff like that.
You can use xfdmaster.library to unpack the most crunch formats.
A long time ago I wrote some little interface for xfdmaster in blitz.
If you want it I can send it to the list. There`s also a shared library
for playing octa med mods but you may better use the one which
comes with blitz.
> 
> Oh yes, I can`t figure a way to recognise a module properly. What I did
was
> looking in the file header which is the same as the filename minus the
.mod
> orso. But that isnt foolproof. Is there a better way to recognise a
> modfile?
That depends on the module format you want to figure out. Octa med
modules start with "MMD"+modformatversion. Protracker mods start
with the song name and have a "M.K." string after the samplenames.
 > 
> Thanks
> 
Regards
-- 
A merry christmas and a happy new year wishes

           Andreas

email: Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de             Software Failure of Airsoft
Softwair, Coder   
