@NODE "Mail_531" "RastPort"
          Tue, 15 Dec 1998 14:20:06 +0000
          15 Dec 98 14:20:07 +0000
From: "S.J.CROY" <ap6013@qmw.ac.uk>
Organization: University of London (QMW)
Date: Tue, 15 Dec 1998 14:19:57 +0000
encoding: 7BIT
Subject: RastPort


Hello again Blitzers,

	Can anyone help me with this little problem? Using the 
nlibs, Ive defined a bitmap, and found the pointers to the plane 
data.  I only want to use the last bitmap for certain drawing 
functions, but Nlibs needs a rastport to do this. Unfortunatly, I don`t 
have a clue how to do this for just one plane.  Any ideas?
  
Cya
Steven



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_532" "Re: RastPort"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    15 Dec 98 15:38:41 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 15 Dec 1998 15:38:26 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: RastPort

> Hello again Blitzers,
> 
>  Can anyone help me with this little problem? Using the 
> nlibs, Ive defined a bitmap, and found the pointers to the plane 
> data.  I only want to use the last bitmap for certain drawing 
> functions, but Nlibs needs a rastport to do this. Unfortunatly, I don`t
> have a clue how to do this for just one plane.  Any ideas?

 Same as with any numbner of plane bitmpa.

Bitmap 0,320,200,1
DEFTYPE._RastPort rp
InitRastPort_ &rp
rp\_BitMap =3D Addr BitMap(0)


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
  d.mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk ICQ=3D16827694
  http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn


