@NODE "Mail_553" "Re: Reading CD ROM ID Numbers"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Tue, 29 Dec 1998 16:03:30 +0000
Organization: Corrupted Software
Subject: Re: Reading CD ROM ID Numbers

I watched as BootBlock/Carnage hammered "Re: Reading CD ROM ID
Numbers" out on their keyboard...

>> Does anybody know how to read the ID numbers that are encoded on
the CD's
>> with Blitz 2?

> While on the subject of CD ROM's, could someone tell me how to read
the
> (C)Copyright/Producer/etc info on CD's?

They aren't on the CD, those are gotten from a CDID file stored on
your hard-disk.  CD's do *not* contain any information about their
contents other than a standard Table of Contents which just contains
data like the offsets of the tracks, nos of tracks etc.

> And maybe how to get the manufactuer (me? Can't spell? Yah right! :)
info of
> the CD drive (SCSI/ATAPI) ?

Don't know, that's something I haven't been able to figure out...

-- 
