@NODE "Mail_554" "Re: Reading CD ROM ID Numbers"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Tue, 29 Dec 1998 16:04:11 +0000
Organization: Corrupted Software
Subject: Re: Reading CD ROM ID Numbers

I watched as Stuart Walker hammered "Reading CD ROM ID Numbers" out on
their keyboard...

> Does anybody know how to read the ID numbers that are encoded on the
CD's
> with Blitz 2?

They aren't stored on the CD, it's a checksum that you arrive at by
taking offsets from the cd and mixing it with nos of tracks etc to
arrive at a number that you stick "ID" in front of.  There's an
example on aminet, in the blitz directory of how to do this, Mavati
something archive I think...

