From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Fri, 18 Dec 1998 08:38:38 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Requesters..

> Hiya.. I'm looking into a project.. and I was wondering how one would go
> about modifying requesters.. instead of having it display "insert disk i=
n
> any drive" instead have it say "Inept IBM user! insert disk "name" in th=
e
> slot right in front of you!"

 I think ASL and ReqTools requesters are both capable of this (RT definate=
ly), 
what you do is set up your requester with the text and the two buttons and=
 some 
IDCMP flags which would also cause the requester to close, in this case 
#IDCMP_DISKINSERTED. Don't know how you'd make them the default system 
requesters though.
 
> or somehting equally fun..

 Like setting fire to their fingers using the patented Grill-o-mouse?

> or evenm have it pop up recoverbale errors with custom messages.. I wann=
a
> pick on a friend.. :)

 Check out DisplayAlert_ in intuition.library, which lets you set an alert=
 
number, string and height of alert.


