@NODE "Mail_578" "Re: Rudimentary Blitzing"
From: Jake Frederick <gonzo@acadia.net>
Date: Fri, 11 Dec 1998 08:47:53 +0500
Subject: Re: Rudimentary Blitzing

On 11-Dec-98, Hrafn wrote:
> Hey all! :)
> 
> Can someone please tell me how to initialise an 8-bit black high-res
> screen?

If your using graphics you'll probably need to use a bitmap on your screen, so
this should work:

    screen 0,8
    bitmap 0,640,200,8
    showbitmap 0
    cls 0   

> I've been fiddling around with the Screen and Cls commands to try and
> create the afformentioned screen but can't seem to make it happen.
> Also, does anyone know what all the parameters in the long format of the
> Screen command are for? My reference manual doesn't seem to explain (or
> does it?).

I think they are in the manual, page 173. Which parameters are you having
trouble with?

-- 
