@NODE "Mail_579" "Rudimentary Blitzing"
From: Hrafn <jhines1@mail.usyd.edu.au>
Date: Fri, 11 Dec 1998 20:33:24 +0500
Subject: Rudimentary Blitzing

Hey all! :)

Can someone please tell me how to initialise an 8-bit black high-res
screen?
(Well, maybe not 8-bit. What's a standard colour depth used in the average
Amiga game? 32 cols?) Can someone send me a list of the colour depth
parameters?? What does the "^" symbol represent when referring to colour
depth?? (eg 2^3 = 8 colours). ??
Questions, questions, questions!! Geez, what a pest! ;)

I've been fiddling around with the Screen and Cls commands to try and
create the afformentioned screen but can't seem to make it happen.
Also, does anyone know what all the parameters in the long format of the
Screen command are for? My reference manual doesn't seem to explain (or
does it?).

Thanks heaps! :)

Omigod! I just unpacked a Blitz2.11 (demo version) archive hidden away
within my hd to discover its interface is displayed in WorkBench 3 style
with system legal menus and gadgets! (Which is what I want!) - as opposed
to this apparently older version I have sporting a blue coloured
non-system-legal title bar and shoddy menus.

Upon loading my current version of Blitz a requester pops up displaying:

----
Blitz Basic 2 Version 2.01
(C)opyright 1995 - Acid Software
Updated Version
----

Whereas the `About' menu item dialog box reads:

----
BLITZ BASIC 2
Release 1.0
(C)opyright 1991 - Acid Software
----

What's going on?! And what's with this Ted Version 1.1 displayed on the
title bar? What's all that about?
Also, the demo version just freezes upon loading. I use an A1200, so is
there an aga-fixed version of Blitz out there?
Can someone pleeeaaase tell me where I can grab a copy of the latest and
greatest version of Blitz Basic! (AGA-fixed; crash-free; with WorkBench 3
appearance!)

My utmost gratitude to anyone who can help me out!
Thanks Blitzworld!

