On the 12th-Dec-1998, Toby Zuijdveld has this to say:

>> If your using graphics you'll probably need to use a bitmap on your
>> this should work:

>>    screen 0,8
>>    bitmap 0,640,200,8
>>    showbitmap 0
>>    cls 0

> That like totally doesn't work on gfx boards tho.  Better to open a window
and
> attach a bitmap to that, I *think*?

How about using a screenmode selector, and then using #ScreenTags# command
to open in the appropriate screenmode.  This should make the whole thing GFX
board friendly.  Of course, you would still need to assign a bitmap to the
screen.  Attached is an example that opens a standard PAL screen (not GFX
board friendly, sorry) with no titlebar, and draws a square on the screen
(and they say the amiga isn't capable of graphical wizardry (;  ).

Regards

Scott

xyz.scott@virgin.net

