Hello Curt.

On 03-Dec-98, Curt Esser wrote:

> The problem I have is that I don't quite understand how the "loop" part=

> works.
> (The routine now just ignores any loop information).
> Does anybody know how to get the loop info and save it too?

How about Reverse Engineering ? Take a sample, Load it into AudioMaster o=
r
something, save the sample with, and without the LOOP on, then compare th=
e
two files, to see the difference ?

> I am "ASM-challenged" myself.

> Translation:  I'm too dumb to code ASM  ;)

Bull, Anyone can code ASM, it's just a matter of time. ASM is on a much
lower level than C or Basic, so all the commands are much simpler to use.=

Offcourse, "dicovering" how to do complex stuff is always tricky :o)

A little hint to optimise your code :o) Use shifts, instead of
multiplying/dividing.

Examples : =


a/2 =3D a LSR 1 - a/4 =3D a LSR 2 - a/8 =3D a LSR 3 a.s.o.
a*2=3D a LSL 1 - a*4 =3D a LSL 2 - a*8 =3D a LSL 3 a.s.o.

You may have known this, you may not. Now you know :o)


Regards
-- =

