@NODE "Mail_587" "scan rates"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 30 Dec 1998 05:26:08 -0500
Subject: scan rates

Hi everyone,

The different Monitors use different scan rates, for example standard PAL =
50HZ and Euro72 = 69HZ

So if I want to count 1 second in PAL, I wait for 50 Vblanks.

If the screen is Euro72, am I correct to wait 69 vblanks to count 1 second?

Thanks...
      
                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




