@NODE "Mail_590" "Re: scan rates"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 30 Dec 1998 18:30:01 -0500
Subject: Re: scan rates

Hi Toby

On 30-Dec-98, Toby Zuijdveld wrote:

> Yup.  But how do you tell what the scanrate for each driver is?

One way is to go into your SYS:Storage/Monitors/ and click on every one you
find.

Now run your screenmode.prefs program, and select each driver you see.  It
will tell you all info about it, including scanrate, maximum sizes,
colours, etc.
Of course this only shows the ones you have on your system.

I am trying to work out how to access this from the screenmode requester. 
I
am sure the information is found in one of the NewType structures, but I
haven't located it yet.

Here is a listing from a source Paul West sent me that might help:


$40120000 ; Cybervision Lores 320x240 ?Hz
   $21000 ; AGA Lores PAL 320x256 non-laced single-scan 50Hz
   $A1000 ; AGA Lores DoublePAL 384x275 non-laced double-scan 48Hz
   $89000 ; AGA Lores Super72 384x290 non-laced single-scan 71Hz
   $11000 ; AGA Lores NTSC 320x200 non-laced single-scan 60Hz
   $39000 ; AGA Lores Multiscan 320x240 double-scan 58Hz
   $59000 ; AGA Lores HighGFX 512x250 non-laced single-scan 54Hz
   $69000 ; AGA Lores Euro72 320x200 non-laced double-scan 69Hz
   $91000 ; AGA Lores DoubleNTSC 384x227 non-laced double-scan 58Hz
   $29004 ; AGA PAL 640x400 Hires laced single-scan 50Hz
   $19004 ; AGA NTSC 640x400 Hires laced single-scan 60Hz
   $39024 ; AGA Multiscan 640x400 Hires non-laced single-scan 58Hz
   $69024 ; AGA Euro72 640x400 Hires non-laced single-scan 69Hz
   $A9004 ; AGA DoublePAL 640x400 Hires non-laced double-scan 48Hz
   $99004 ; AGA DoubleNTSC 640x400 Hires non-laced double-scan 58Hz


<sb>

Thanks to everybody who tested the screenmode requester I posted.  I have it
all working now, thanks to Paul West.  Someone had asked me for a copy of
this, but I lost the mail  :(   Whoever it was, please mail me and I will
send it to you.


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
