Hello Curt.

On 30-Dec-98, Curt Esser wrote:

> The different Monitors use different scan rates, for example standard P=
AL
=3D
> 50HZ and Euro72 =3D 69HZ

> So if I want to count 1 second in PAL, I wait for 50 Vblanks.

> If the screen is Euro72, am I correct to wait 69 vblanks to count 1
second?

In theory yes. In practice no. Using different tools (VGAOnly for exsamle=
MonEd is another good one) you can change the scanrates of your displays.=

Now if someone has a PIV they can use whatever scanrate the feel like.


