>> So if I want to count 1 second in PAL, I wait for 50 Vblanks.
>> 
>> If the screen is Euro72, am I correct to wait 69 vblanks to count 1
>> second?
>  
>    I think someone said you still get ticks in PAL or NTSC (depending
> what mode you boot up in), even when using GFX card screenmodes- can
> any one settle this one!

Yes, I have seen this too.  So which is correct?  I can't test as I can only
use standard PAL (50hz) & NTSC (60hz) modes here.

Actually even better would be if someone knows how to access the CIA timer
to be able to read seconds/microseconds in the same way as using ResetTimer
and Ticks commands.

I have a source that shows how to do a Delay_ type thing with the CIA timer,
but this doesn't help much.  I need to know how many seconds have passed at
certain points, without stopping the program.
> 
>  Ps: why is it called Euro72 when it's 69hz- it should be called
> Euro69- oh I see...    ;>

