@NODE "Mail_594" "Re: scan rates"
From: Toby Zuijdveld <hotcakes@abacus.net.au>
	Blitz List <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Thu, 31 Dec 1998 15:25:22 +0500
Organization: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Res=A1stance?=
Subject: Re: scan rates
Encoding: quoted-printable

On 31-Dec-98, Curt Esser set out across the seas with this message:

->Actually even better would be if someone knows how to access the CIA
->to be able to read seconds/microseconds in the same way as using
->and Ticks commands.

Hey, I know!  This seems too obvious to be true, tho, so tell me if I've
missed something...

Use the #SystemDate# and #Seconds# commands inside a loop to count the nu=
mber
of #Ticks# that have passed since the last second passed!

<pseudo-example, probably won't work just as is>

b.b=3D0
a.b=3D#Seconds#
#While# a=3D#Seconds#
   ;   #VWait#   ;   Might wanna use that if you're in AMIGA mode
#Wend#   ;   That was to make sure you've waited for a complete second
a=3D#Seconds#   ;   to pass, first...
#ResetTimer#
#While# a=3D#Seconds#
   b+1
   #VWait#
#Wend#

Tada!  b=3Dnumberofticks per second

Again, there's probably something really wrong with that idea that I just=

didn't think of ;]

-- =


