> just didn't think of ;]

   Good idea, but I don't think it'd be accurate enough, I remember
someone saying the timer lib wasn't that accurate- and obviously you'd
have to make sure that the correct screen was up the whole time, and
that the user didn't switch from say NTSC to PAL in the middle of your
program which would screw everything up!
  The only reliable way is to use the CIA timer- I've got an OS friendly
example from the DEV CD, but I haven't gotten around to attempting to
convert it to Blitz (it's in C). I can send it to anyone who wants it.
 
