@NODE "Mail_596" "Screen structure"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 22 Dec 1998 03:48:54 -0500
Subject: Screen structure

Hi Everyone,

I am opening a screen with a taglist, using the standard overscan settings
(ie, the ones the user set in their overscan prefs) to properly fill the
screen.

This works fine, but now I need to know the width & height of the screen I
just opened.

I know I can get this from the screen structure, but I do not know the names
of the NewTypes in the screen structure.  Does anybody have a listing of
this?

Or at least how to get the width & height?

Thanks, and Happy Holidays.


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_597" "Re: Screen structure"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    22 Dec 98 10:02:50 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 22 Dec 1998 10:02:46 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Screen structure

On 22 Dec 98, at 3:48, Curt Esser wrote:

> This works fine, but now I need to know the width & height of the screen=
 I
> just opened.

 If you used OS commands then you'd have a pointer to your screen so use:
	*scr\Width
	*scr\Height

 If you used Blitz commands to open the screen you'd need to do (with 
amigalibsii.res):
	*scr._Screen =3D Peek.l(Addr Screen(#screennum))
before you used the above two variables.


