@NODE "Mail_612" "Re: Sound thging"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 08 Dec 1998 06:42:47 -0500
Subject: Re: Sound thging

Hi Garry

On 07-Dec-98, Garry Newman wrote:
> 
> Ive got a letter off Mark Moran
> 
> He asks about the setperiod command
> 
> is it possible to get more than 2 notes out of it or something
> 
> any help?

You should be able to get any note you want from it.  But there is a bug in
the debugger - it won't let you use any values >15, which is useless.  Most
sounds have a default period of 300 >

So, you must have the debugger off when using Setperiod.

Or use FREQ, which does the same thing, but it is used AFTER the sound is
played, and DOES NOT alter the actual period set in the sound object...

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_613" "Re: SoundFx"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 01 Dec 1998 18:14:48 -0500
Subject: Re: SoundFx

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1748017328.1

Hi amorel

> Another thing was, in order to recognise that a file is, say a mmd1
> mod(octamed) u need to read the first 4 digits of the header, which says
> mmd1 or sth like that. No matter what I tried, it would refuse to read it
> properly. Any idea?

Here is a bit of code I have used to identify 4 channel med mods.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748017328.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="medID.asc"

If ReadFile(0,newmod$)
    FileInput 0
    A$ = Edit$(12)    ; Read 12 bytes or upto a chr$(10)
    CloseFile 0
    Use Window 0
    If Left$(A$,3)= "MMD" AND Right$(A$,1) = "4"  ; OK, 4 channel MED

--BOUNDARY.1748017328.1--




