@NODE "Mail_637" "Re: System Font name,...."
          release (PO203-101c) ID# 0-0U10L2S100) with SMTP id AAA438
          for <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>; Thu, 17 Dec 1998 12:34:08 +0000
From: "Xyz Scott" <xyz.scott@virgin.net>
Subject: Re: System Font name,....
Date: Thu, 17 Dec 1998 12:37:30 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

On the 17-Dec-1998, Loki announced to the world:

>   Ok so I can grab the system`s font height,.... BUT,.. How do I get the
>name of the system font so that I can load it into my program
>with #LoadFont#??


OK.  Try this:

*ThisScreen.Screen=Peek.l(Addr Screen (ScreenNo))
FontName$=Peek$(*ThisScreen\Font\ta_Name)
FontSize.b=*ThisScreen\Font\ta_YSize

...where ScreenNo is the screen number of the workbench screen.
By the way, you will need amigalibs.res for this to work.

Regards

Scott

xyz.scott@virgin.net




