> What is it excactly you want to know ? Doing a poke ?Var_01,<whatever> will
> change it (to <whatever>). However, IMHO you should use variables instead.
> Unless of course you need your values to be unsigned. Also, there is little
> point in using the even command if you declare any byte types, as the
> memory will then again be offsat on an odd byte, and you will have to
> insert a pading byte afterwards.

`Even' doesn't add 1 to the address, it crops the lower bit from the
address and [if necessary] adds 2 to it to ensure it is a multiple of
2.

-- 
