@NODE "Mail_670" "Re: Wierd Listwiev stuff."
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 30 Dec 1998 20:44:15 -0500
Subject: Re: Wierd Listwiev stuff.
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hi Mikkel

On 30-Dec-98, Mikkel L=F8kke wrote:
> Hello.
> =

> Is it just me or are all listviews (GadTools type) created a few pixels=

> short ? In the program I'm doing ATM, I open a gtlistview which is
supposed
> to be innerwidth pixels high. Which it isn't. Does it have something to=

do
> with truncating the size to fit all the entries ?

No, it has to do with the height of the font being used.  The listview
always shows even lines of text (you will never see an entry in the
listview cut in half by the bottom border) so it actually will open in a
size that exactly matches with the font size, rather than necessarily to
the height you have set.

The way I get around this is to adjust the height of the window to match =
the
height of the listview.  See my "text reader in a window" example for how=
 I
did this (it really puts the textfile into a GTlistview gadget)

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
