@NODE "Mail_674" "Re: Would YOU like a new Blitz Compiler?"
From: "Matthew Parsons" <billyray@enterprise.net>
Organization: Private User
Date: 4 Dec 98 21:02:45 +0000
Subject: Re: Would YOU like a new Blitz Compiler?
Encoding: 7bit

To Be honest I prefer Fredericks system too, but my system will save
more time in the long run, as it will require no recompilation of the
libs should a new cpu be used.

Since starting this project, I have realised (through some test
compiles) that my system will not produce very efficient code :(.

It looks like I might evolve my compiler a little and I might lose my
bilayer system altogether. Even though it's without a doubt the better
system :).


