 via smail with P:esmtp/R:smart_host/T:smtp
	(sender: <Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de>) 
	id <m0ztXa8-001nxfC@insider.regio.net>
	for <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>; Fri, 25 Dec 1998 14:47:08 +0100 (MET)
	(Smail-3.2.0.101 1997-Dec-17 #1 built DST-Jul-17)
From: Andreas Falkenhahn <Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de>
Date: Fri, 25 Dec 1998 14:20:32 +0100
Organization: Airsoft Softwair
Subject: xfdmaster.library stuff for Blitz

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1749598496.1

Hi !!

Here`s some stuff for xfdmaster.library use in blitz:

1) xfdmaster.library1  : the fd-converted library. Libnum is 196.
                                          Create your own one if the number
isn`t free!
2) xfdmaster.res  : the resident file created from the SAS/C includes
3) xfdmaster.asc  : some little demo how to decrunch a file using xfdmaster

These things were done some time ago and might be of some
interest...probably...otherwise please don`t kill me :)
Have fun with the stuff....and report me any problems ;-)

-- 
A merry christmas and a happy new year wishes

           Andreas

email: Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de             Software Failure of Airsoft
Softwair, Coder   
WWW: http://www.airsoft.home.pages.de      A1200/040T, 40mhz, 2.0GB HD, 18MB
Ram, 33.600 Modem          

"Windows95 is bug free" Bill Gates in `95...."We fixed over 5000 bugs since
the release of Win95" Bill Gates in`98
"AMiGA iS BACK......BACK FOR THE FUTURE!", Pedro Tyschtschenko on the Theme
of Amiga CD


--BOUNDARY.1749598496.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="xfdmaster.asc"
Encoding: quoted-printable

;
; xfdmaster.library example code
;
; done by Andreas Falkenhahn <Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de>
;
; cleaned up for blitz list on christmas :-)
;
; have fun
;
; Additional notes:
;
; - don`t forget to load xfdmaster.res resident
; - aswell as amigalibs.res
; - OpenLibrary() is not necessary because blitz does
;   all this for you if you work with converted fd`s
;   (so don`t wonder if you don`t find any xfdmasterbase
;    related routines in here.........)
;

; Insert filenames here
decrfrom$ =3D "dh3:musik/classic/mod.aladdin"       ; file to decrunch
decrto$   =3D "t:decrunchedfile"                    ; destination file

*bufinf.xfdBufferInfo=3DxfdAllocObject_(#XFDOBJ_BUFFERINFO)
If *bufinf
  If ReadFile(0,decrfrom$)
    NPrint "Opening file "+decrfrom$+"..."
    FileInput 0
    *myfilesize.l=3DLof(0)
    *filebuf.l=3DAllocMem_(*myfilesize,#MEMF_PUBLIC)
    ReadMem 0,*filebuf,*myfilesize
    CloseFile 0
    *bufinf\xfdbi_SourceBuffer=3D*filebuf
    *bufinf\xfdbi_SourceBufLen=3D*myfilesize
    If xfdRecogBuffer_(*bufinf)
      If *bufinf\xfdbi_PackerFlags AND (#XFDPFF_PASSWORD OR #XFDPFF_KEY16=
 OR #XFDPFF_KEY32)
        NPrint "Error! File is password protected!"
        End
      EndIf
      *bufinf\xfdbi_TargetBufMemType=3D#MEMF_PUBLIC ; don`t forget this!!=
!!
      If xfdDecrunchBuffer_(*bufinf)
        *targetlen.l=3D*bufinf\xfdbi_TargetBufSaveLen
        *targetbuf.l=3D*bufinf\xfdbi_TargetBuffer
        *targetcru.l=3D*bufinf\xfdbi_PackerName
        NPrint "Decrunching "+Chr$(34)+Peek$(*targetcru)+Chr$(34)+" file =
to "+decrto$+" ("+Str$(*targetlen)+" bytes)..."
        If WriteFile(0,decrto$)
          FileOutput 0
          WriteMem 0,*targetbuf,*targetlen
          CloseFile 0
        Else
          NPrint "Error writing file!"
        EndIf
        FreeMem_ *bufinf\xfdbi_TargetBuffer,*bufinf\xfdbi_TargetBufSaveLe=
n
        xfdFreeObject_ *bufinf
        DefaultOutput
        NPrint "Done!"
      Else
        NPrint "Error decrunching file!"
        End
      EndIf
    Else
      NPrint "Error recognizing buffer!"
    EndIf
  Else
    NPrint "Error reading file!"
  EndIf
Else
 NPrint "Error allocating object!"
 End
EndIf

End   ; und tschuess



--BOUNDARY.1749598496.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="xfdmaster.res"
Encoding: base64

AAAD8wAAAAAAAAABAAAAAAAAAAAAAAo0AAAD6QAACjQACQAAAB4AAAAAABgAAvy4HHhmZG1f
